00:21:45,817 --> 00:21:48,224
like carefree children of a happy God.

243
00:21:48,528 --> 00:21:52,739
We're going to rejoice that inside
of us lives the veritable spirit

244
00:21:52,866 --> 00:21:55,866
of the everlasting
redeeming Christ, Jesus.

245
00:21:55,994 --> 00:21:58,567
- Hallelujah!
- Praise the Lord!

246
00:22:03,793 --> 00:22:08,005
Bill, see how many of those dear people
can match God's bountiful gift

247
00:22:08,131 --> 00:22:09,708
with their own offerings.

248
00:22:09,841 --> 00:22:14,467
You darlings can't make milk,
and God just won't make money.

249
00:22:15,138 --> 00:22:19,385
? Stand up, stand up for Jesus

250
00:22:19,684 --> 00:22:23,931
? Ye soldiers of the cross

251
00:22:24,063 --> 00:22:28,013
? Lift high His royal banner

252
00:22:28,151 --> 00:22:30,523
No preaching tonight. No sermonising.

253
00:22:30,653 --> 00:22:33,939
No sad faces or tears, just happiness.

254
00:22:34,574 --> 00:22:35,689
Tomorrow...

255
00:22:35,825 --> 00:22:38,612
tomorrow is the last night
of our revival here,

256
00:22:38,745 --> 00:22:41,615
but when I leave,
you're going to carry on my work.

257
00:22:41,748 --> 00:22:45,496
You're all of you evangelists,
every blessed one of you.

258
00:22:45,627 --> 00:22:49,921
Shake hands with the person on your
right. Go on! Ask them if they're saved.

259
00:22:50,048 --> 00:22:52,206
Won't you shake hands for Jesus?

260
00:22:52,342 --> 00:22:55,675
Bless you, brother.
Sing, everybody! Sing his praises!

261
00:22:55,804 --> 00:22:59,172
- Sister Falconer!
- Won't you find happiness in Jesus?

262
00:22:59,307 --> 00:23:02,676
It's happiness to hear your wondrous
message. Can I have a moment?

263
00:23:02,811 --> 00:23:05,480
Excuse me, please. Excuse me.

264
00:23:06,439 --> 00:23:08,681
- Excuse me, please.
- Thank you, brother.

265
00:23:08,817 --> 00:23:12,731
Oh, uh, yes... Sorry. No change.

266
00:23:12,862 --> 00:23:14,902
Thank you.

267
00:23:24,123 --> 00:23:26,163
(car horn)

268
00:23:33,174 --> 00:23:35,297
I picked some flowers for you.

269
00:23:35,426 --> 00:23:39,424
Sister, my son saw the Virgin Mother
on the roof last night after your sermon.

270
00:23:39,556 --> 00:23:41,180
Can you spare me an hour?

271
00:23:41,307 --> 00:23:45,175
I simply can't. Aren't our counsellors
taking care of you? Sister Rachel?

272
00:23:45,311 --> 00:23:49,475
Sister Rachel, see what you can do. Every
one of these lovely people is important.

273
00:23:49,607 --> 00:23:53,356
- May I have your names, please?
- I must congratulate you again.

274
00:23:53,486 --> 00:23:55,028
- Thank you.
- I'm a preacher.

275
00:23:55,155 --> 00:23:57,906
- I know how inspired you must've been.
- What church?

276
00:23:58,032 --> 00:24:01,781
What church? Well, uh, at present,
I don't exactly have a church, but...

277
00:24:01,911 --> 00:24:04,485
What is it this time, brother?
Booze or women?

278
00:24:04,622 --> 00:24:07,113
Why, Sister Falconer. Me?

279
00:24:07,834 --> 00:24:10,407
Whichever one it is,
you have my blessing. Jim?

280
00:24:10,545 --> 00:24:13,462
- Uh, Sister, I, uh...
- Nice try, brother.

281
00:24:20,472 --> 00:24:23,638
- Will prayer cure diabetes?
- Would you give me your address?

282
00:24:23,766 --> 00:24:25,724
- Sister?
- Just a moment.

283
00:24:25,852 --> 00:24:28,010
- What denomination?
- I must talk to you.

284
00:24:28,146 --> 00:24:32,144
- If you'll just leave your name.
- I have an important message for you.

285
00:24:32,275 --> 00:24:34,481
A message? From Sister Falconer?

286
00:24:34,611 --> 00:24:36,936
- I heard you sing last night.
- Oh?

287
00:24:37,071 --> 00:24:40,238
I know flattery don't mean much
to a talented person like you,

288
00:24:40,366 --> 00:24:43,284
but when you sang that
inspiring song "Beulah Land",

289
00:24:43,411 --> 00:24:45,949
it made me realise that music
is the voice of love.

290
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:48,571
- Oh.
- And what is love?

291
00:24:48,708 --> 00:24:51,460
Love is the morning and the evening star.

292
00:24:51,586 --> 00:24:54,670
America. A land of great opportunity.

293
00:24:54,797 --> 00:24:58,249
Take me. I've been with the Central
States Appliance Company a year.

294
00:24:58,384 --> 00:25:02,762
I'm their crack salesman already. They
wanna make me a partner. It's a great life.

295
00:25:02,889 --> 00:25:08,096
Folks in 14 states know me by my
first name. Makes a fella feel humble.

296
00:25:08,228 --> 00:25:12,177
- Would you like to start with a cocktail?
- A cocktail in the middle of the day?

297
00:25:12,315 --> 00:25:16,858
Don't you know that drinkin' is sinful
and against the principles of Coolidge?

298
00:25:16,986 --> 00:25:18,267
I meant shrimp cocktail.

299
00:25:18,404 --> 00:25:21,192
Just bring us some of
Mother's apple pie and coffee.

300
00:25:21,324 --> 00:25:22,699
Yes, sir.

301
00:25:24,035 --> 00:25:26,028
I'm sorry.

302
00:25:27,121 --> 00:25:30,953
Tell me, when did you
first start servin' God?

303
00:25:31,084 --> 00:25:36,042
Two years ago. In Cato, Missouri. Sister
Sharon's gospel singer got hurt in a riot.

304
00:25:36,172 --> 00:25:39,707
A riot? In a Christian town like...
What was the name?

305
00:25:39,843 --> 00:25:41,088
Cato.

306
00:25:41,219 --> 00:25:45,632
Cato, Missouri. Yes, some roughnecks
started yellin' and screamin' and hollerin'.

307
00:25:45,765 --> 00:25:47,176
During the services?

308
00:25:47,308 --> 00:25:52,551
Sister Sharon yelled to a farmer on our
side "Hit him one for the Lord, brother!"

309
00:25:52,689 --> 00:25:55,809
Apple pie. They ought to write
a song about apple pie.

310
00:25:55,942 --> 00:25:58,611
A gospel song. And you should sing it.

311
00:26:22,635 --> 00:26:24,758
(whistle blows)

312
00:26:24,888 --> 00:26:27,129
(conductor) All aboard!

313
00:26:37,525 --> 00:26:40,775
- Godspeed the good work, Sister!
- Good luck, Sister Sharon!

314
00:26:40,904 --> 00:26:43,774
Godspeed, Sister Sharon! Good luck!

315
00:26:59,130 --> 00:27:00,874
Shara?

316
00:27:01,007 --> 00:27:05,336
Our advance man in Lincoln, Nebraska,
got drunk, and he's disappeared.

317
00:27:05,470 --> 00:27:08,091
No more business tonight.

318
00:27:10,266 --> 00:27:14,560
- Thank heavens. When I didn't see you...
- Thinkin' about you every second.

319
00:27:14,687 --> 00:27:18,555
The fire department in Lincoln say
that we can't put up a tent our size.

320
00:27:18,691 --> 00:27:22,392
- The church committee are bickering...
- Please, Bill.

321
00:27:23,488 --> 00:27:25,813
The gentleman with Sister Falconer.

322
00:27:25,949 --> 00:27:27,609
- Mr Morgan?
- Yes.

323
00:27:27,742 --> 00:27:32,036
Tell him Mr Lefferts would like to see him
out back on the observation platform.

324
00:27:32,163 --> 00:27:34,203
Thank you, sir.

325
00:27:53,059 --> 00:27:55,680
Mr Lefferts? My name is Gantry.

326
00:27:56,771 --> 00:27:58,479
Congratulations.

327
00:27:58,606 --> 00:28:01,276
- Sorry I woke you up.
- Then why did you do it?

328
00:28:01,401 --> 00:28:03,228
Oh, I recognised you.

329
00:28:03,361 --> 00:28:07,145
I had to congratulate you on those
articles you wrote about evolution.

330
00:28:07,448 --> 00:28:11,363
Not only scarifyin' and sensational,
but very funny.

331
00:28:12,871 --> 00:28:17,912
Tell me somethin', Jim boy. I know
you got one of them Pulitzer prizes,

332
00:28:18,042 --> 00:28:21,791
but you don't really believe in
all that evolution junk, now do you?

333
00:28:21,921 --> 00:28:24,922
- Devoutly.
- Then you must believe

334
00:28:25,049 --> 00:28:29,462
- that God himself is a gorilla.
- How did you arrive at that conclusion?

335
00:28:29,596 --> 00:28:33,296
It says in the Bible
"God created man in his own image."

336
00:28:45,445 --> 00:28:48,695
Sister Sharon -
she's pretty important news, eh?

337
00:28:49,574 --> 00:28:51,946
What's your interest in her?

338
00:28:54,204 --> 00:28:56,576
- Can I be frank with you?
- Try.

339
00:28:56,956 --> 00:29:00,824
- She fascinates me.
- You'll have to get in line.

340
00:29:01,127 --> 00:29:05,291
You also have to get over
a hurdle first, name of Bill Morgan.

341
00:29:05,423 --> 00:29:09,884
Say, I almost forgot. He's comin' out
to see you, right about now.

342
00:29:10,011 --> 00:29:12,632
He's got some secret information.

343
00:29:18,645 --> 00:29:21,266
Thanks a lot, Jim boy. Thanks a lot.

344
00:29:29,614 --> 00:29:32,366
- You all right?
- Yes, fine. I was just wondering...

345
00:29:32,492 --> 00:29:34,734
Later, honey.

346
00:29:49,217 --> 00:29:51,542
I'm sorry, this seat is taken.

347
00:29:51,678 --> 00:29:54,085
Even the Lord never turned
his back on a sinner.

348
00:29:54,222 --> 00:29:58,089
I am not the Lord, but I am tired.
Now, will you please go away?

349
00:30:00,728 --> 00:30:05,604
You weren't so tired and all of life
two years ago in Cato, Missouri.

350
00:30:06,025 --> 00:30:09,560
- That's where we met.
- Met?

351
00:30:09,696 --> 00:30:12,862
Yes. On a Friday night, it was.
Remember? Remember the riot?

352
00:30:12,991 --> 00:30:17,451
Some roughnecks got to whoopin'
and hollerin' and fightin', and you yelled

353
00:30:17,579 --> 00:30:20,200
- "Hit him one for the Lord!"
- That's what I said.

354
00:30:20,331 --> 00:30:24,115
And that's exactly what I did.
I busted him one for the Lord.

355
00:30:24,252 --> 00:30:27,004
Oh, it was a lovely fight!

356
00:30:31,009 --> 00:30:35,053
When I saw you in Cato, I thought I was
seein' an angel, and you haven't changed.

357
00:30:35,180 --> 00:30:38,050
- A very tired angel.
- It's no wonder,

358
00:30:38,183 --> 00:30:42,430
givin' everybody else hope and courage,
nobody to lean on yourself.

359
00:30:42,562 --> 00:30:46,061
I suppose this is a generous offer
to let me lean on you.

360
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:50,401
I wouldn't have the nerve, Sister.

361
00:30:50,528 --> 00:30:52,070
- Yesterday, Mr...
- Gantry.

362
00:30:52,197 --> 00:30:54,236
..you said you were a preacher.

363
00:30:54,365 --> 00:30:59,241
Well, uh, practically, yes. Uh, you see,
the semester I was to be ordained...

364
00:30:59,370 --> 00:31:01,944
They kicked you out of college.

365
00:31:02,081 --> 00:31:05,497
Well, it was a... a tragedy, kind of.

366
00:31:05,627 --> 00:31:07,666
A girl.

367
00:31:08,588 --> 00:31:10,296
Yeah. A girl.

368
00:31:12,300 --> 00:31:13,759
A girl named Lulu Bains.

369
00:31:13,885 --> 00:31:17,633
- Does she work for you, or you for her?
- We work together.

370
00:31:17,764 --> 00:31:22,805
Would it be unethical to ask just what
you'll write about Sister Sharon?

371
00:31:22,936 --> 00:31:25,059
- It would.
- Oh?

372
00:31:25,188 --> 00:31:27,857
- I'm sorry.
- She's brilliant.

373
00:31:27,982 --> 00:31:30,355
"Inspired" is a more appropriate word.

374
00:31:30,485 --> 00:31:34,020
- It means "touched by the hand of God".
- Precisely.

375
00:31:34,155 --> 00:31:36,362
Now, get the picture.

376
00:31:36,491 --> 00:31:41,034
It's Christmas Eve. God's pure snow
driftin' down, and joy in the air.

377
00:31:41,162 --> 00:31:45,326
I enter the Schoenheim church
late at night to pray for guidance.

378
00:31:45,458 --> 00:31:48,495
And what do I find, right behind the altar?

379
00:31:48,628 --> 00:31:51,748
Lulu Bains, my betrothed, my bride-to-be,

380
00:31:51,881 --> 00:31:57,255
half-naked, locked in the arms of
her lover, a cardsharp from Chicago.

381
00:31:58,346 --> 00:32:02,973
A couple of years later he was bumped
off in a gang war, God rest his soul.

382
00:32:03,101 --> 00:32:06,517
Well, that's it, I guess.
I lost all interest in religion.

383
00:32:06,646 --> 00:32:09,137
But when I saw you,
it was like a call from beyond.

384
00:32:09,274 --> 00:32:11,646
Could I see you again?
Have breakfast with me?

385
00:32:11,776 --> 00:32:15,145
What's your hotel room number
in Lincoln, hm? Tell me.

386
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:21,116
You're so completely... so outrageous.
I... I think I like you.

387
00:32:21,244 --> 00:32:24,198
I guess I've been around
sanctimonious folks too long.

388
00:32:24,330 --> 00:32:27,699
You're amusing,
and you smell like a real man.

389
00:32:29,794 --> 00:32:33,246
Yes, I'll meet you by my tent.
That's where I breakfast. Good night.

390
00:32:33,381 --> 00:32:36,216
- Oh, but, Sister...
- Oh, this time I mean it.

391
00:32:37,886 --> 00:32:39,925
Pleasant dreams.

392
00:32:43,975 --> 00:32:49,811
Evening, Brother Morgan. Oh, I wouldn't
bother her now. She's resting, poor child.

393
00:32:56,446 --> 00:33:02,365
The wind will come from there, so keep
the centre poles where you've got them.

394
00:33:02,494 --> 00:33:05,945
That way the canvas won't snap
and crackle all through the sermon.

395
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,120
Here they come.

396
00:33:10,210 --> 00:33:13,045
Morning, Sister! Jim boy!
A lovely morning it is.

397
00:33:13,171 --> 00:33:15,377
- Good morning.
- I woke with a terrific idea.

398
00:33:15,507 --> 00:33:17,464
Later. Good morning, Captain.

399
00:33:17,592 --> 00:33:20,842
- You can't erect that tent here, ma'am.
- Why not?

400
00:33:20,970 --> 00:33:22,928
- Fire laws.
- Nonsense.

401
00:33:23,056 --> 00:33:25,428
No, ma'am. No nonsense
at all. No, ma'am.

402
00:33:25,558 --> 00:33:28,393
"Ma'am" is a contraction for "madam".
I am not a madam,

403
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:32,019
a calibre of woman I'm sure you
know well and do business with.

404
00:33:32,148 --> 00:33:34,722
How many have been put out
of business by fire laws?

405
00:33:34,859 --> 00:33:38,727
- Your tent holds over 1,000 people...
- Captain, this is Mr Lefferts,

406
00:33:38,863 --> 00:33:43,157
- a reporter for the Zenith Times-DisPatch
- Zenith? Welcome. This is Fire Chief...

407
00:33:43,284 --> 00:33:47,033
Isn't it a fact, Mr Lefferts, that the whisky
big shots want me closed down?

408
00:33:47,163 --> 00:33:50,200
They certainly don't think
you do their business any good.

409
00:33:50,333 --> 00:33:55,244
Know why? I'm not afraid to fight whisky
and repeal with police help or without it.

410
00:33:55,380 --> 00:33:59,212
- If you're accusing me of not...
- I am. Do you enforce Prohibition?

411
00:33:59,342 --> 00:34:00,587
I certainly do.

412
00:34:00,718 --> 00:34:04,134
How many speakeasies could you
take the captain to in his home town?

413
00:34:04,264 --> 00:34:07,929
- Without a membership card? 50.
- (Sharon) Fire laws!

414
00:34:08,059 --> 00:34:10,384
Do you see any of my workmen smoking?

415
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:13,011
Do you mind? This might start a fire.

416
00:34:13,148 --> 00:34:16,682
- If they don't smoke inside...
- You're welcome to see tonight.

417
00:34:16,818 --> 00:34:20,234
A little bit of salvation
will do you both some good.

418
00:34:22,282 --> 00:34:27,193
Sister Sharon! Never did I ever see
anybody handle the cops the way you did.

419
00:34:27,328 --> 00:34:30,828
All right. What's this terrific idea
you woke up with?

420
00:34:30,957 --> 00:34:35,370
Yes, well... How would it be if I addressed
your meetin' as a saved businessman?

421
00:34:35,503 --> 00:34:38,837
I could talk on the hard,
practical dollars-and-cents value

422
00:34:38,965 --> 00:34:41,882
of Christ in commerce.

423
00:34:42,010 --> 00:34:44,252
Tom, slacken off that rope. It's too tight.

424
00:34:44,387 --> 00:34:47,258
By the way, what is
your business? Hold-ups?

425
00:34:47,390 --> 00:34:50,011
You're a card. I sell
for Central Appliances.

426
00:34:50,143 --> 00:34:53,559
- Don't you like your job?
- Why, sure. It's a great life.

427
00:34:53,688 --> 00:34:57,935
I'm their crack salesman. Only last month
they wanted to make me a junior partner.

428
00:34:58,067 --> 00:35:03,109
Would you believe that people in 14 states
call me by my first name? Elmer.

429
00:35:06,826 --> 00:35:10,491
No use kiddin' you, is there?
It's no life at all.

430
00:35:10,622 --> 00:35:13,955
Filthy, dreary hotel rooms.
Always chasin' trains.

431
00:35:15,210 --> 00:35:19,706
Always tellin' dirty stories
to keep the buyers laughin'.

432
00:35:19,839 --> 00:35:23,208
Always the pint bottle
to prove you're a sport.

433
00:35:23,343 --> 00:35:28,384
That kind of fella's no success at all.
He's just a tramp in a silk shirt.

434
00:35:28,515 --> 00:35:30,139
Well...

435
00:35:33,561 --> 00:35:38,354
I could tell the sinners
I'm a... I'm a salesman, just like that.

436
00:35:39,776 --> 00:35:43,275
I come into one of them...
miserable hotel rooms.

437
00:35:44,364 --> 00:35:47,069
I'm discouraged.
I got no sales to chalk up.

438
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:49,987
Nothin' to read. I'm lonely.

439
00:35:50,620 --> 00:35:55,780
I'm just dyin' for a drink. Some of them
salesmen drink somethin' terrible.

440
00:35:55,917 --> 00:36:00,912
And I reach my hand into
a dresser drawer... and what do I find?

441
00:36:02,006 --> 00:36:04,877
A Gideon Bible. That's what I find.

442
00:36:05,009 --> 00:36:07,679
Yes. Yes, go on.

443
00:36:08,888 --> 00:36:14,475
I reached my hand into a dresser drawer,
and I found a Gideon Bible.

444
00:36:14,602 --> 00:36:15,634
(man) Louder!

445
00:36:15,770 --> 00:36:18,261
I found a Gideon Bible.

446
00:36:18,398 --> 00:36:21,767
I was so lonely and miserable,
I might as well have been in hell.

447
00:36:21,901 --> 00:36:25,401
I was in hell. I knew
all the salesman's tricks.

448
00:36:25,530 --> 00:36:28,531
Why wasn't I rich?
Why wasn't I successful?

449
00:36:28,658 --> 00:36:32,276
I opened the Bible,
and I read the 18th Psalm.

450
00:36:33,705 --> 00:36:36,410
"The Lord is my rock and my fortress."

451
00:36:37,375 --> 00:36:40,411
"The Lord is my fortress."
Do you hear that? The Lord.

452
00:36:40,545 --> 00:36:43,083
- Praise the Lord!
- The Lord is my rock!

453
00:36:43,214 --> 00:36:45,752
The next mornin'
I walked into a general store.

454
00:36:45,884 --> 00:36:48,920
"What are you sellin' today?
Gold-plated vacuum cleaners?"

455
00:36:49,179 --> 00:36:52,713
"No, sir. You can get better vacuum
cleaners at Sears and Roebuck,

456
00:36:52,849 --> 00:36:56,894
and you can get 'em cheaper, but
you can't beat our electric toasters."

457
00:36:57,020 --> 00:36:59,725
He sat down and wrote me
the biggest order of the year.

458
00:36:59,856 --> 00:37:01,184
(man) Hallelujah!

459
00:37:01,649 --> 00:37:04,899
Can you hear me, Lord? Thank you, Lord.

460
00:37:05,028 --> 00:37:08,444
I didn't make that sale, Lord.
You did. Thank you.

461
00:37:11,784 --> 00:37:13,824
(man) Hallelujah!

462
00:37:14,787 --> 00:37:17,195
And when I told my pals...

463
00:37:17,332 --> 00:37:21,460
when I told my pals I was
comin' to Jesus, they laughed.

464
00:37:21,586 --> 00:37:24,124
But Sister Falconer didn't laugh.

465
00:37:24,255 --> 00:37:27,042
She said "Go ahead, brother.
Give 'em hell."

466
00:37:27,175 --> 00:37:29,666
I'm going to give you
all the hell in the Bible,

467
00:37:29,803 --> 00:37:33,717
and if you don't like it, fix it up with
the Lord because the Lord put it there.

468
00:37:33,848 --> 00:37:35,592
Listen to me, sinners.

469
00:37:35,809 --> 00:37:37,682
Listen to me, sinners.

470
00:37:37,811 --> 00:37:42,722
You can't pray to kingdom come
and play bridge or poker. And, Mother,

471
00:37:42,857 --> 00:37:46,641
you can't say your psalms and look
at God through the bottom of a beer mug.

472
00:37:46,778 --> 00:37:47,809
And you, brother,

473
00:37:47,946 --> 00:37:52,572
you can't go to church on Sunday
and cheat at business on Monday.

474
00:37:52,700 --> 00:37:57,576
We're comin' back to you, God. We're
comin' back to the old-time religion!

475
00:38:01,793 --> 00:38:04,498
And what is religion?

476
00:38:04,629 --> 00:38:06,752
What is religion?

477
00:38:06,881 --> 00:38:09,004
Religion is love.

478
00:38:09,134 --> 00:38:11,969
And love is the morning
and the evening star.

479
00:38:12,095 --> 00:38:14,847
Love, the eternal glorious musicmaker.

480
00:38:14,973 --> 00:38:18,258
Love! Not the carnal love,
but the divine love.

481
00:38:18,393 --> 00:38:23,185
And where does this great love
come from? It comes direct from God!

482
00:38:27,443 --> 00:38:30,361
I admit I'm not smart like some of them...

483
00:38:30,488 --> 00:38:34,533
some of them smart-alecky professors,
wise-guy writers and agitators.

484
00:38:34,659 --> 00:38:38,787
I know nothing of theosophy, philosophy,
psychology, ideology or any other ology.

485
00:38:38,913 --> 00:38:40,621
But I know this.

486
00:38:40,748 --> 00:38:45,909
With Christ, you're saved,
and without him, you're lost.

487
00:38:46,045 --> 00:38:48,334
And how do I know
there's a merciful God?

488
00:38:48,464 --> 00:38:51,584
Because I've seen the devil
plenty of times!

489
00:39:06,274 --> 00:39:08,943
Any punk ball player
can make a slide like that.

490
00:39:09,068 --> 00:39:12,603
But how many folks have got the guts
to play ball on God's team?

491
00:39:12,739 --> 00:39:18,160
And listen to this. The captain
of that team is Jesus Christ himself.

492
00:39:18,286 --> 00:39:20,326
So, come on, man, woman, child.

493
00:39:20,455 --> 00:39:23,906
Who'll be the first
to shake hands for Jesus?

494
00:39:24,542 --> 00:39:26,582
Come on, now! Everyone!

495
00:39:29,797 --> 00:39:34,127
Are you gonna make me beg and beg
when I'm offerin' you my Jesus?

496
00:39:35,345 --> 00:39:39,841
Did the Saviour die in vain?
Did he suffer on the cross for nothin'?

497
00:39:39,974 --> 00:39:42,928
Argh! My God, I can't stand it!

498
00:39:43,061 --> 00:39:45,386
Oh, my God, no! Not any more!

499
00:39:45,522 --> 00:39:49,733
Sinner, I'll fight you every day in the week
for God and twice on Sundays!

500
00:39:49,859 --> 00:39:53,193
Help me. Brother Gantry, save me.
I sin every day!

501
00:39:53,321 --> 00:39:56,488
Tell me what to do, please.
Tell me what to do!

502
00:39:57,450 --> 00:40:00,321
- "Lifeline."
- (band Plays and PeoPle sing)

503
00:40:01,204 --> 00:40:03,909
? Throw out the lifeline

504
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:09,497
? Somebody's drifting away

505
00:40:09,629 --> 00:40:12,381
? Throw out the lifeline

506
00:40:12,590 --> 00:40:15,212
? Throw out the lifeline

507
00:40:16,469 --> 00:40:19,256
Bless you for bringing us
such a wonderful man.

508
00:40:19,389 --> 00:40:22,509
- Sister Sharon.
- Bless you, Brother Gantry.

509
00:40:22,642 --> 00:40:26,770
You've changed my whole life.
You're such a good man.

510
00:40:35,238 --> 00:40:37,943
- This light supposed to be kept burnin'?
- Yep.

511
00:40:38,074 --> 00:40:42,535
Sometimes folks come just to touch
where Sister Sharon stands.

512
00:40:43,496 --> 00:40:46,201
Say, I heard you talk tonight.

513
00:40:46,332 --> 00:40:50,496
- How'd you like it?
- Mister, I've been converted five times.

514
00:40:50,628 --> 00:40:56,215
Billy Sunday, Reverend Biederwolf, Gypsy
Smith, and twice by Sister Falconer.

515
00:40:57,177 --> 00:41:00,759
I get terrible drunk,
and then I get good and saved.

516
00:41:00,889 --> 00:41:05,597
Both of them done me a powerful lot
of good - gettin' drunk, and gettin' saved.

517
00:41:05,727 --> 00:41:07,766
Well, good night.

518
00:41:23,077 --> 00:41:25,747
Are you praying, or planning to take over?

519
00:41:25,872 --> 00:41:27,496
Shara!

520
00:41:28,833 --> 00:41:31,455
Did I do all right?
I mean, did I do all right for you?

521
00:41:31,586 --> 00:41:34,753
Yes, you were fine. Really fine.
I cried like everybody else.

522
00:41:34,881 --> 00:41:37,336
No, but... Tell me the truth, please.

523
00:41:37,467 --> 00:41:41,050
450 converts out of 1200 people?

524
00:41:41,179 --> 00:41:43,717
That's a truth of some kind.

525
00:41:45,433 --> 00:41:48,849
- Morgan thought you were vulgar.
- Do you?

526
00:41:48,978 --> 00:41:50,686
- Think I'm vulgar?
- Yes.

527
00:41:50,814 --> 00:41:52,224
- But you like me.
- Yes.

528
00:41:52,357 --> 00:41:54,599
- Very much.
- Not very much.

529
00:41:56,194 --> 00:41:57,818
Shara.

530
00:42:26,057 --> 00:42:27,255
Forgive me, Sharon.

531
00:42:27,392 --> 00:42:31,224
- You've got me plumb hypnotised.
- No, you're just hungry, that's all.

532
00:42:31,354 --> 00:42:34,355
But I can hypnotise, because
God chose me to do his work.

533
00:42:34,482 --> 00:42:36,807
- Sure, me too.
- No.

534
00:42:36,943 --> 00:42:41,237
I chose you. The big difference
between you and me is that I believe.

535
00:42:41,364 --> 00:42:43,404
I really believe.

536
00:42:45,702 --> 00:42:48,323
- You'd like to join us, wouldn't you?
- Oh, yes.

537
00:42:48,454 --> 00:42:52,404
- Report at nine. We'll discuss salaries...
- I got swell ideas for promotions.

538
00:42:52,542 --> 00:42:56,290
- Radio, the third ear of the human race...
- You smoke, don't you?

539
00:42:56,421 --> 00:42:59,837
- Well...
- I can smell it. Will you stop it altogether?

540
00:42:59,966 --> 00:43:01,875
- Well, yes...
- The drinking, too?

541
00:43:02,010 --> 00:43:04,927
- Oh, sure. If that's what you want, I...
- It is.

542
00:43:05,054 --> 00:43:07,094
Good night.

543
00:43:16,608 --> 00:43:18,849
Evening, Brother Gantry.

544
00:43:20,820 --> 00:43:25,363
Jim boy! Say, all the time Shara and me -
uh, Sister Falconer and me...

545
00:43:25,492 --> 00:43:28,113
Yep. Sitting right over there.

546
00:43:28,244 --> 00:43:33,535
- You're not gonna write about this?
- Boy kisses girl? Hell, that's not news.

547
00:43:33,666 --> 00:43:37,878
You're slipping, brother. You know,
when you first hooked me on that train,

548
00:43:38,004 --> 00:43:43,509
I thought you were a friendly,
likeable, self-respecting first-class bum.

549
00:43:43,635 --> 00:43:47,467
And now... now look at you.
Where'd you get your style?

550
00:43:49,140 --> 00:43:53,470
- Just let her rip, I guess.
- I've heard powerful Bible-wallopers,

551
00:43:53,603 --> 00:43:57,814
but you not only put the fear of God
into them, you scared the hell out of 'em.

552
00:43:57,941 --> 00:44:01,938
And the way you strung certain words
together - "America, home, mother".

553
00:44:02,070 --> 00:44:05,486
"Heaven, hell... Love, hate, sin".

554
00:44:05,615 --> 00:44:11,071
You know, it's a funny thing, Jim.
I get up here and I... I see them out there.

555
00:44:12,372 --> 00:44:15,788
Next thing you know,
I'm howlin', they're moanin'.

556
00:44:15,917 --> 00:44:18,455
It's like a mighty spirit
movin' inside of me.

557
00:44:18,586 --> 00:44:24,340
Words and ideas come pourin' out
like... like riled-up strangers.

558
00:44:24,467 --> 00:44:28,761
I feel so powerful and full of love,
I'm about to explode.

559
00:44:28,888 --> 00:44:30,928
I do explode.

560
00:44:31,057 --> 00:44:34,806
And then I just about love everybody

561
00:44:36,855 --> 00:44:39,096
Especially the girls.

562
00:44:41,985 --> 00:44:46,647
Yes, this is where I belong, all right.
Right here, in religion.

563
00:44:46,781 --> 00:44:48,821
Even if it is a tent.

564
00:44:48,950 --> 00:44:51,523
Every circus needs a clown,
Brother Gantry.

565
00:44:51,661 --> 00:44:57,248
And you might turn out to be the funniest
clown of 'em all. And the most successful.

566
00:44:58,334 --> 00:44:59,959
Clown!

567
00:45:00,962 --> 00:45:03,168
Jim boy, you're terrific. Terrific.

568
00:45:09,804 --> 00:45:13,387
Some of them smart-aleck college
professors are trying to prove

569
00:45:13,516 --> 00:45:16,553
that this here ape is your
great-great-grandfather.

570
00:45:16,686 --> 00:45:19,094
Come back here. Let folks see you.

571
00:45:19,230 --> 00:45:23,643
Well, he might be Darwin's uncle,
but he certainly ain't yours or mine.

572
00:45:23,776 --> 00:45:25,816
Right, Grandpop?

573
00:45:43,588 --> 00:45:46,755
Just a monkey, folks. Just a monkey.

574
00:45:48,009 --> 00:45:50,678
Would Jesus play poker?

575
00:45:50,804 --> 00:45:53,804
Would St Paul play the stock market?

576
00:45:53,932 --> 00:45:57,632
What do you think will get you
into God's own glorious heaven?

577
00:45:57,769 --> 00:45:59,892
This ace of spades?

578
00:46:00,021 --> 00:46:01,978
Your bank book?

579
00:46:02,106 --> 00:46:04,977
Or this pledge to be a good Christian?

580
00:46:07,821 --> 00:46:10,775
Sin, sin, sin.

581
00:46:10,907 --> 00:46:15,035
You're all sinners!
You're all doomed to perdition.

582
00:46:16,246 --> 00:46:20,326
You're all goin' to
the painful, stinkin', scaldin',

583
00:46:20,458 --> 00:46:23,293
everlastin' tortures of a fiery hell,

584
00:46:23,419 --> 00:46:26,207
created by God for sinners, unless...

585
00:46:27,173 --> 00:46:28,881
unless...

586
00:46:29,008 --> 00:46:32,876
unless you repent!
Repent with Sister Falconer!

587
00:46:33,012 --> 00:46:35,052
(howls)

588
00:46:40,061 --> 00:46:42,433
(barks)

589
00:46:44,023 --> 00:46:46,693
Let that man alone! Let him alone!

590
00:46:47,527 --> 00:46:50,943
Go ahead and bark, brother.
Go right ahead and bark!

591
00:46:51,072 --> 00:46:55,070
There he is! The devil!
Bark that devil outta this tent!

592
00:46:55,702 --> 00:46:57,741
(rhythmic claPPing)

593
00:47:12,719 --> 00:47:17,879
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

594
00:47:23,646 --> 00:47:27,098
(Morgan) ..the most disgusting display
of bad taste in my experience.

595
00:47:27,233 --> 00:47:30,982
A human barking dog.
A monkey in the pulpit.

596
00:47:31,112 --> 00:47:33,983
It's preposterous.
That's why it can't go on.

597
00:47:34,115 --> 00:47:39,026
And it's obvious to everyone - even
dangerous. Especially before Jim Lefferts.

598
00:47:39,162 --> 00:47:42,862
And our newspaper friend...
He's about as friendly as a rattlesnake.

599
00:47:42,999 --> 00:47:46,783
- Then you think it's wrong.
- Not wrong. Ridiculous.

600
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:49,790
One minute you're preaching
a happy, perfumed heaven,

601
00:47:49,923 --> 00:47:53,422
the next, Gantry's damning everyone
to a scalding, stinking hell.

602
00:47:53,551 --> 00:47:56,920
- I'd say we make a pretty good team.
- Yes.

603
00:47:57,055 --> 00:48:00,258
Yes, like two cops
working over a criminal.

604
00:48:00,391 --> 00:48:04,638
Gantry scares him with the electric chair,
you save him if he confesses.

605
00:48:04,979 --> 00:48:08,728
The point is, our sinner does confess,
and he is saved.

606
00:48:10,318 --> 00:48:14,232
- (Morgan) But it was ridiculous.
- Does the method really matter?

607
00:48:16,366 --> 00:48:21,407
Who is this, uh, this Elmer Gantry?
And what do you really know about him?

608
00:48:22,997 --> 00:48:25,323
His background, his reputation?

609
00:48:25,458 --> 00:48:29,207
What does he want?
Money? My job? You? What?

610
00:48:29,337 --> 00:48:32,753
- Bill...
- In 1917, Mr Gantry

611
00:48:32,882 --> 00:48:35,753
was expelled from
a theological seminary in Kansas

612
00:48:35,885 --> 00:48:38,637
for seducing
the deacon's daughter in the church

613
00:48:38,763 --> 00:48:42,677
where he had that day
delivered a Christmas sermon.

614
00:48:42,809 --> 00:48:45,382
And there's more. Do you wanna hear it?

615
00:48:45,520 --> 00:48:47,845
Ta-da!

616
00:48:48,773 --> 00:48:51,893
Ladies and gentlemen,
you see before you a magic carpet.

617
00:48:52,026 --> 00:48:56,190
A heavenly summons.
A ticket to the big time. Listen to this.

618
00:48:56,322 --> 00:48:59,822
"Would you consider meeting with
the church committee and myself

619
00:48:59,951 --> 00:49:04,779
about bringing your revival to our fair city
of Zenith, capital of America's Midwest?"

620
00:49:04,914 --> 00:49:08,829
"Kindly telegraph reply immediately.
Signed, George F Babbitt, Secretary,

621
00:49:08,960 --> 00:49:12,495
Zenith Chamber of Commerce,
Chairman of the Church Board."

622
00:49:12,630 --> 00:49:13,460
Zenith.

623
00:49:13,590 --> 00:49:16,507
- We're not ready for Zenith.
- Mr Babbitt thinks we are.

624
00:49:16,634 --> 00:49:19,801
I know we are. Next stop, Zenith.
Then Chicago, New York, London.

625
00:49:19,929 --> 00:49:22,634
Straight to the top
on the Sharon Falconer Express!

626
00:49:22,765 --> 00:49:25,601
- In a tent? They'll laugh at us.
- Not at Shara.

627
00:49:25,727 --> 00:49:29,427
It's pitchman's talk. What do you know
about the background of our work?

628
00:49:29,564 --> 00:49:32,648
The nature of revivalism is rural.
It grew out of frontier life.

629
00:49:32,775 --> 00:49:36,144
- Big-city people are more cynical...
- They're more sinful, too.

630
00:49:36,279 --> 00:49:38,984
And more lonely
and more unhappy. And...

631
00:49:39,115 --> 00:49:41,737
And, Shara, they need you more.

632
00:49:44,496 --> 00:49:47,580
- I'm against this.
- Bill boy, you're an old sourpuss.

633
00:49:47,707 --> 00:49:51,657
- This is a passport to the Promised Land.
- Gantry, I am not your boy.

634
00:49:52,170 --> 00:49:55,586
You deluded her, but to me,
everything about you's offensive.

635
00:49:55,715 --> 00:50:00,922
You're a crude, vulgar show-off, and
your vocabulary belongs in an outhouse.

636
00:50:09,646 --> 00:50:11,056
Crude.

637
00:50:11,189 --> 00:50:12,813
Vulgar.

638
00:50:13,900 --> 00:50:19,060
Show-off, huh? You know something?
You're right, Bill. Let's put it this way.

639
00:50:19,364 --> 00:50:23,444
You're a five-dollar textbook.
Me, I'm a two-cent tabloid newspaper.

640
00:50:23,576 --> 00:50:25,652
You're too good for the people.

641
00:50:25,787 --> 00:50:29,785
I am the people. Sure, I'm common -
just like most people.

642
00:50:30,583 --> 00:50:33,999
The common people put Christianity
on the map in the first place.

643
00:50:34,295 --> 00:50:38,589
What are you saying, Shara?
That you want to go to Zenith? Now?

644
00:50:39,884 --> 00:50:42,885
I wonder what God wants.

645
00:50:44,139 --> 00:50:48,302
All right, Shara. All right.
Maybe you are ready for Zenith.

646
00:50:48,434 --> 00:50:52,764
- Thank you. I'll be with you in a minute.
- Just think of it, Shara. Zenith.

647
00:50:54,566 --> 00:50:57,483
I think the answer to Mr Babbitt
ought to come from you.

648
00:50:57,610 --> 00:51:02,438
Tell 'em we're ready to talk, but they gotta
act fast. Only don't say it as crude as that.

649
00:51:02,574 --> 00:51:07,449
No, no. I'll use some of my
sweet-smelling five-buck words, huh?

650
00:51:07,579 --> 00:51:09,536
I knew we could work together.

651
00:51:09,664 --> 00:51:13,993
Gantry, uh... I just hope you don't
have any ideas about who's boss.

652
00:51:14,127 --> 00:51:15,751
Boss?

653
00:51:15,879 --> 00:51:19,164
Why, the boss is God.
I'm just his messenger boy.

654
00:51:20,592 --> 00:51:23,546
I'm sure God will be relieved.

655
00:51:23,678 --> 00:51:25,386
Yes.

656
00:51:25,513 --> 00:51:29,593
- Leave the money matters to me.
- If they get a guarantee, what do we get?

657
00:51:29,726 --> 00:51:32,015
- Why is cash necessary at all?
- Order!

658
00:51:32,145 --> 00:51:35,229
Gentlemen, without a guarantee,
a revival is impossible.

659
00:51:35,356 --> 00:51:36,103
Kee-rect!

660
00:51:36,232 --> 00:51:42,021
As chairman, I can say I want the revival,
but we're ministers, not financiers.

661
00:51:42,155 --> 00:51:44,860
- I agree. After all, $30,000...
- Will be raised.

662
00:51:44,991 --> 00:51:47,909
- How, Mr Babbitt?
- By decent, respectable people

663
00:51:48,036 --> 00:51:50,574
- who want to see old-time religion...
- I agree.

664
00:51:50,705 --> 00:51:52,863
- Please let me finish.
- Of course, George.

665
00:51:52,999 --> 00:51:54,992
- Thank you, Charlie.
- OK, then.

666
00:51:55,126 --> 00:51:57,451
Everybody knows that I contribute more

667
00:51:57,587 --> 00:52:01,585
to charity and poverty and things
than anybody, hm?

668
00:52:01,716 --> 00:52:06,212
Hey, now, didn't my real-estate company
give you that corner lot rent-free

669
00:52:06,346 --> 00:52:11,506
for your church baseball team, huh? Hm?
And I'm not even a Methodist! (laughs)

670
00:52:12,644 --> 00:52:18,231
All right, then. I always say, business
is business - that's the American way!

671
00:52:18,358 --> 00:52:21,727
- Now, if you boys...
- Why do you want a revival in Zenith?

672
00:52:21,861 --> 00:52:26,108
Oh, I know what you're gettin' at, Phil.
You don't fool me for a second.

673
00:52:26,241 --> 00:52:29,989
- We're aware of the financial problems.
- Are we aware, sir?

674
00:52:30,119 --> 00:52:33,405
- My church hasn't been painted for years.
- Whose fault is that?

675
00:52:33,540 --> 00:52:35,449
What about the gymnasium?

676
00:52:35,583 --> 00:52:38,786
In my area, getting milk for
the children is the problem.

677
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:41,921
Your problem is
empty churches, gentlemen.

678
00:52:42,048 --> 00:52:43,839
That is a fact.

679
00:52:43,967 --> 00:52:47,383
The fact is that church attendance
is falling off everywhere.

680
00:52:47,512 --> 00:52:51,973
Sister Falconer can fill your churches.
That's why you're here in the first place.

681
00:52:52,100 --> 00:52:53,927
- Kee-rect!
- Tea, Mr Babbitt?

682
00:52:54,060 --> 00:52:57,928
- I always say, if you're sick, call a doctor.
- I agree.

683
00:52:58,064 --> 00:53:00,982
Now, uh, let's look at
the record, gentlemen.

684
00:53:01,109 --> 00:53:05,272
Sister Sharon has been in Lincoln -
this is going on the fifth week now.

685
00:53:05,405 --> 00:53:08,690
275 new church members,

686
00:53:08,825 --> 00:53:11,031
- in one church alone.
- My church.

687
00:53:11,161 --> 00:53:14,743
More than 2700
decisions for Christ, gentlemen.

688
00:53:14,873 --> 00:53:18,822
Actual converts who signed pledges.
Not our statistics,

689
00:53:18,960 --> 00:53:21,795
but printed in
your own Zenith newspaper.

690
00:53:21,921 --> 00:53:25,705
And written up by... by Jim Lefferts,
a Pulitzer prizewinner.

691
00:53:25,842 --> 00:53:30,255
Does the record show how long your
converts remain church members?

692
00:53:30,889 --> 00:53:34,589
Well, I always say,
when in doubt, take action.

693
00:53:35,268 --> 00:53:36,513
- Let's vote.
- Second.

694
00:53:36,644 --> 00:53:37,676
- All in favour?
- Aye.

695
00:53:37,812 --> 00:53:40,434
- Uh, just a moment, please.
- You're out of order.

696
00:53:40,565 --> 00:53:43,732
- There's a motion on the floor.
- May I say something, please?

697
00:53:43,860 --> 00:53:46,481
You have our...
undivided attention, Sister.

698
00:53:46,613 --> 00:53:51,773
Wouldn't it be a much happier world if
money was not the third arm of religion?

699
00:53:51,910 --> 00:53:54,994
He can't paint his church.
You can't have your gymnasium.

700
00:53:55,121 --> 00:53:57,446
No child should be without milk.

701
00:53:57,749 --> 00:54:01,877
And my expenses are high enough to run
a factory - I practically do run a factory.

702
00:54:02,003 --> 00:54:06,748
Who do you think pays for my staff? The
musicians, the men who put up the tent.

703
00:54:06,883 --> 00:54:11,960
Truck transportations, railroad fares,
food bills. Advertising and printing bills.

704
00:54:12,096 --> 00:54:15,845
Electric bills, insurance bills, hotel bills.

705
00:54:15,975 --> 00:54:19,344
The church committees always
expect a contribution from me,

706
00:54:19,479 --> 00:54:25,268
and they always get it. And when I leave
town five weeks later, you get the benefit.

707
00:54:25,401 --> 00:54:29,102
You have the flock,
and I have to start all over again.

708
00:54:31,157 --> 00:54:34,491
No, gentlemen, you don't want a revival.

709
00:54:35,662 --> 00:54:38,532
And I'm afraid you don't want me, either.

710
00:54:48,508 --> 00:54:52,375
I think these gentlemen would like
a little privacy to kick things around.

711
00:54:52,512 --> 00:54:54,670
- Thank you, Mr Gantry.
- Excuse me.

712
00:54:54,806 --> 00:54:57,641
I'm not ashamed to admit
our churches are half-empty.

713
00:54:57,767 --> 00:55:00,970
- The ball parks are full.
- So are the races.

714
00:55:01,354 --> 00:55:02,433
Let's vote.

715
00:55:02,564 --> 00:55:06,264
Vote to do what? Marry the Church
to a three-ring circus?

716
00:55:06,401 --> 00:55:08,939
To barkers who say
they're messengers of God?

717
00:55:09,070 --> 00:55:13,483
Who reduce frightened farmers to howling
dogs? All very entertaining, I'm sure.

718
00:55:13,616 --> 00:55:16,820
We are in competition
with the entertainment business.

719
00:55:16,953 --> 00:55:19,824
- I'm not.
- Then you ought to be. Huh?

720
00:55:20,915 --> 00:55:22,742
How about your bingo games?

721
00:55:22,876 --> 00:55:25,876
And how about your baseball games
and square dances?

722
00:55:26,004 --> 00:55:28,921
Now, ain't that entertainment?
What's the difference?

723
00:55:29,048 --> 00:55:33,129
It's up to us to make a success out of
Christianity, keep the churches full.

724
00:55:33,511 --> 00:55:37,094
What has religion
to do with filling churches?

725
00:55:37,223 --> 00:55:40,639
Once there were only
13 Christians in the entire world.

726
00:55:40,768 --> 00:55:44,184
Was Christianity a failure?
Did God go out of business?

727
00:55:44,314 --> 00:55:50,269
Kee-rect! Christianity is a going concern,
a successful international enterprise.

728
00:55:50,778 --> 00:55:53,400
If you boys don't get
young people back into church,

729
00:55:53,531 --> 00:55:56,201
if you don't keep the train on the tracks,

730
00:55:56,326 --> 00:56:00,026
your church boards are gonna
find somebody else who will.

731
00:56:00,163 --> 00:56:02,832
Isn't that clear, Reverend Garrison?

732
00:56:08,713 --> 00:56:12,925
Speaking for myself,
not my congregation or its church board,

733
00:56:13,051 --> 00:56:16,883
religion is not a business.
And revivalism is not religion.

734
00:56:17,013 --> 00:56:19,053
And my vote is no.

735
00:56:20,975 --> 00:56:23,727
- Good night, gentlemen.
- Phil!

736
00:56:24,103 --> 00:56:25,728
Harvard!

737
00:56:26,606 --> 00:56:31,813
Well, look around you, boys. Young folks
crying out they're the lost generation.

738
00:56:31,945 --> 00:56:37,283
Godless anarchists on every street
corner, and he walks out on a crisis.

739
00:56:37,408 --> 00:56:42,201
Do you realise that practically
every president of the United States

740
00:56:42,330 --> 00:56:44,239
was a Mason and a Protestant?

741
00:56:44,374 --> 00:56:47,043
And every session of Congress
opens with a word

742
00:56:47,168 --> 00:56:49,659
from the King James version of the Bible.

743
00:56:49,796 --> 00:56:54,672
And right now, in our enlightened age,
a Catholic is running for president.

744
00:56:54,801 --> 00:56:56,295
- Mr Babbitt...
- And...

745
00:56:56,427 --> 00:56:57,838
Mr Babbitt!

746
00:56:59,097 --> 00:57:01,339
Don't say another word.

747
00:57:06,020 --> 00:57:08,511
George, I agree with you.

748
00:57:09,649 --> 00:57:12,318
Please, John.
If revivalism can do the job...

749
00:57:12,443 --> 00:57:13,772
Paul.

750
00:57:13,903 --> 00:57:18,612
Zenith had a revival 40 years ago.
It saved everybody in sight for miles,

751
00:57:18,741 --> 00:57:21,363
but today we still have
the same problems.

752
00:57:21,494 --> 00:57:23,653
Please, John.

753
00:57:23,788 --> 00:57:24,951
Please.

754
00:57:25,039 --> 00:57:27,246
(Babbitt) Order, order. Now, now, now.

755
00:57:27,375 --> 00:57:31,289
Gentlemen, if you'll only
leave the money matters to me.

756
00:57:33,590 --> 00:57:34,752
Kee-rect!

757
00:57:34,883 --> 00:57:36,922
(knocking at door)

758
00:57:43,016 --> 00:57:46,848
- Welcome to Zenith, Sister.
- Congratulations. A wise decision.

759
00:57:46,978 --> 00:57:52,185
Gentlemen, all your churches will be
closed while the revival is in progress.

760
00:58:18,343 --> 00:58:22,257
- Great folks, aren't they?
- Swell, George, just swell.

761
00:58:33,316 --> 00:58:38,393
When Sister Falconer says "Shake hands
for Jesus", the chorus starts singing.

762
00:58:38,530 --> 00:58:42,823
- Brother Gantry...
- Just a sec. Ushers wear these badges.

763
00:58:42,951 --> 00:58:45,905
The minute folks start comin' in,
you go into action.

764
00:58:46,037 --> 00:58:50,366
Keep 'em movin'. Get pledge cards into
their hands, and don't forget the pencils.

765
00:58:50,500 --> 00:58:54,711
Now, you counsellors, you'll wear
these lapel pennants. Pretty, eh?

766
00:58:54,838 --> 00:58:58,503
German-speaking, hold up your hands.
Swedish-speaking? Fine.

767
00:58:58,633 --> 00:59:01,753
Ask if they're regular church
members. Also, what church.

768
00:59:01,886 --> 00:59:07,047
And it don't matter what church. Now,
some folks are gonna wanna cry. Let 'em.

769
00:59:09,269 --> 00:59:10,811
"God is love."

770
00:59:10,937 --> 00:59:12,728
Jim-dandy, huh?

771
00:59:12,856 --> 00:59:16,805
Well, that's it, I guess.
Tonight's the big night.

772
00:59:16,943 --> 00:59:20,775
Are we gonna make a touchdown for
Jesus Christ? Any further questions?

773
00:59:20,905 --> 00:59:24,274
- Brother Gantry...
- OK, then. At 7.30, we hit the line.

774
00:59:24,409 --> 00:59:28,157
God is love. Sister Sharon's sanctuary.
May I help you?

775
00:59:28,288 --> 00:59:31,372
Yes, sir, that's right.
Every evening at 8.30.

776
00:59:31,499 --> 00:59:34,868
Yes, you may take a trolley car.
The line's 14th Street.

777
00:59:35,003 --> 00:59:38,952
Yes. Yes, I understand.
Well, if you're lonesome and restless,

778
00:59:39,090 --> 00:59:43,633
Sister Sharon recommends that
you read Psalm 23 or Psalm 27.

779
00:59:46,598 --> 00:59:49,883
Do you know of a better
product to sell than God?

780
00:59:51,644 --> 00:59:53,933
Uh, Sister, one more question.

781
00:59:54,063 --> 00:59:56,851
- I'm sorry, what was that question again?
- I said...

782
00:59:56,983 --> 00:59:59,854
Sister, in what branch
of the Church were you baptised?

783
00:59:59,986 --> 01:00:02,228
Hold it, Sister!

784
01:00:02,363 --> 01:00:06,147
Sister, I'm afraid you have a problem
with the fire department again.

785
01:00:06,284 --> 01:00:08,193
- The fire department?!
- Bill!

786
01:00:08,328 --> 01:00:11,245
- I've got the chief on the phone.
- Oh, Sister...

787
01:00:11,372 --> 01:00:14,124
- Excuse me.
- ..could I just ask one more question?

788
01:00:14,250 --> 01:00:17,536
What you'll be wearing
for the opening night?

789
01:00:19,756 --> 01:00:23,540
You looked as if you had about enough
of "who, what, when, where".

790
01:00:23,676 --> 01:00:25,716
Thank you.

791
01:00:27,388 --> 01:00:29,844
May I have some water, please?

792
01:00:33,394 --> 01:00:36,099
- You tired?
- Oh, these last two days.

793
01:00:39,651 --> 01:00:42,106
The aspirin age.

794
01:00:42,237 --> 01:00:45,107
Nervous about opening tomorrow night?

795
01:00:48,034 --> 01:00:51,284
- I don't know.
- What about Gantry?

796
01:00:53,248 --> 01:00:57,080
He's got all the nerve
in the world, but no nerves.

797
01:00:59,546 --> 01:01:04,884
You want to know the truth?
I'm scared to death of you city people.

798
01:01:05,009 --> 01:01:09,588
Don't be. The women will worship you,
and the men will love you.

799
01:01:10,598 --> 01:01:12,924
And you?

800
01:01:13,059 --> 01:01:15,182
I'll be there, too.

801
01:01:17,647 --> 01:01:20,055
Good night.

802
01:01:20,567 --> 01:01:22,191
Good night.

803
01:01:26,823 --> 01:01:31,734
Just as sure as God plagued the earth
with pestilence and locusts,

804
01:01:31,870 --> 01:01:34,491
you and I... to doom!

805
01:01:35,290 --> 01:01:40,746
I tell you, the end of the world is comin'.
It's coming this September 15th!

806
01:01:40,879 --> 01:01:45,587
- It says so in the Bible!
- Revivals are against organised labour!

807
01:01:45,717 --> 01:01:48,208
(congregation sings "Marching to Zion")

808
01:01:55,602 --> 01:01:58,721
(college boys sing
"The Star-SPangled Banner")

809
01:02:08,156 --> 01:02:12,782
Hallelujah! The Lord's name be praised!
Stop it, you scallywags! Stop!

810
01:02:26,132 --> 01:02:29,501
Come on, boys.
All right, the locomotive. Here we go.

811
01:02:29,636 --> 01:02:31,628
(whistle) Boom!

812
01:02:32,263 --> 01:02:34,303
(whistle) Boom!

813
01:02:35,016 --> 01:02:38,302
- Sis-boom, Sister!
- Play Sister's introduction.

814
01:02:38,436 --> 01:02:40,310
Sis-boom, Sister!

815
01:02:40,438 --> 01:02:42,680
(band Plays)

816
01:02:42,816 --> 01:02:44,393
Captain Holt!

817
01:02:44,526 --> 01:02:46,602
(? "The Battle Hymn of the RePublic")

818
01:02:46,736 --> 01:02:49,061
Arrest them. Arrest all of them.

819
01:02:49,197 --> 01:02:53,859
I don't know who started the fuss inside.
The ones outside ain't breakin' any laws.

820
01:02:53,993 --> 01:02:57,445
- First arrest them. Then we'll find out...
- I wouldn't do that.

821
01:02:57,580 --> 01:02:59,537
You wanna start a riot?

822
01:02:59,666 --> 01:03:03,200
Folks have gotta have
stretchin' room for their feelings.

823
01:03:03,336 --> 01:03:07,797
Now, why don't you sit down
and get close to God? lt'll be all right.

824
01:03:07,924 --> 01:03:08,706
It's OK.

825
01:03:08,842 --> 01:03:13,338
? Glory, glory, hallelujah

826
01:03:13,555 --> 01:03:17,504
? Glory, glory, hallelujah

827
01:03:17,642 --> 01:03:23,229
? His truth is marching on

828
01:03:23,356 --> 01:03:27,769
? Glory, glory, hallelujah

829
01:03:27,986 --> 01:03:32,648
? Glory, glory, hallelujah

830
01:03:35,160 --> 01:03:41,198
- They're ready for you, Shara.
- You certainly promoted us into Zenith.

831
01:03:41,332 --> 01:03:45,377
You certainly filled our tent,
didn't you? But with what?

832
01:03:45,503 --> 01:03:49,501
You and your people.
Those aren't people. They're a mob.

833
01:03:49,632 --> 01:03:54,590
They're one big animal. I'm not letting
Shara go out there to be humiliated.

834
01:03:54,721 --> 01:03:58,801
And what's your plan? To run?
Where? Back to the sticks?

835
01:03:58,933 --> 01:04:02,978
If we don't win them over tonight,
there'll be no place to run.

836
01:04:03,104 --> 01:04:06,972
- Shara, you've got to face them.
- And do what? Blow them kisses?

837
01:04:07,108 --> 01:04:11,936
Tell them all to be nice little boys
and girls? No, Gantry. No. No.

838
01:04:12,071 --> 01:04:15,986
Zenith is your idea.
Those are your people. You face 'em.

839
01:04:23,249 --> 01:04:24,827
They want Shara.

840
01:04:26,836 --> 01:04:28,912
Listen to me, Shara.

841
01:04:29,047 --> 01:04:32,131
Big-city people have got
a coat of hard varnish,

842
01:04:32,258 --> 01:04:36,090
but underneath, they're just as sick
and scared as anybody else.

843
01:04:36,221 --> 01:04:41,595
People everywhere are the same
in one thing - they're all afraid to die.

844
01:04:41,726 --> 01:04:45,225
They hope you can save them.
And you can, Shara.

845
01:04:46,898 --> 01:04:48,937
You can.

846
01:04:49,692 --> 01:04:52,148
You can, Shara.

847
01:04:52,278 --> 01:04:54,567
You can.

848
01:04:54,697 --> 01:04:56,737
You can, Shara.

849
01:04:58,243 --> 01:05:00,282
You can.

850
01:05:04,123 --> 01:05:07,872
(college boys) Hip, hip, hooray!
Hip, hip, hooray!

851
01:05:08,002 --> 01:05:10,244
Hip, hip, hooray!

852
01:05:11,464 --> 01:05:13,504
(boys cheer)

853
01:05:23,434 --> 01:05:25,676
(singing dies out)

854
01:06:00,263 --> 01:06:02,635
Some of you are troubled.

855
01:06:04,726 --> 01:06:06,683
Sceptical...

856
01:06:06,811 --> 01:06:08,851
of my motives.

857
01:06:10,440 --> 01:06:12,646
You want to know my credentials.

858
01:06:13,610 --> 01:06:15,152
Who am I?

859
01:06:15,778 --> 01:06:18,020
Who sent me?

860
01:06:18,615 --> 01:06:22,031
Some of you have come
to sit in judgement of me.

861
01:06:23,536 --> 01:06:28,779
But who among you is wise enough
to be a judge in the house of God?

862
01:06:30,877 --> 01:06:36,084
For even though you speak with the
tongue of an angel and have not charity,

863
01:06:36,216 --> 01:06:38,671
you are as sounding brass.

864
01:06:41,888 --> 01:06:43,927
If I have sinned...

865
01:06:45,558 --> 01:06:47,800
then God will punish me.

866
01:06:50,271 --> 01:06:53,640
If I am lost in the wilderness,

867
01:06:53,775 --> 01:06:56,645
then God will show me the way back.

868
01:06:59,322 --> 01:07:01,991
Will you pray with me for guidance?

869
01:07:03,743 --> 01:07:05,985
Will you?

870
01:07:08,039 --> 01:07:11,408
God won't mind if you get
a little dirt on your knees!

871
01:07:11,543 --> 01:07:14,116
(old man) I believe in you, Sister.

872
01:07:14,629 --> 01:07:18,247
- Oh, bless you, brother.
- I believe in you, Sister.

873
01:07:18,383 --> 01:07:21,503
(choir sings "What a Friend
We Have in Jesus")

874
01:07:24,430 --> 01:07:26,589
No. No. No music.

875
01:07:27,183 --> 01:07:30,433
Please. Please, no singing, no music.

876
01:07:30,562 --> 01:07:32,601
Let us just pray.

877
01:07:33,898 --> 01:07:36,140
Will you pray with me?

878
01:08:00,717 --> 01:08:02,756
Dearest God...

879
01:08:10,185 --> 01:08:13,139
Are you too proud to kneel, Mr Lefferts?

880
01:08:14,397 --> 01:08:17,398
You may not believe in God...

881
01:08:17,525 --> 01:08:19,981
but God believes in you.

882
01:08:44,677 --> 01:08:46,717
Dear God...

883
01:08:50,683 --> 01:08:54,017
I am set upon by enemies
and I know not why.

884
01:08:56,272 --> 01:09:01,515
The Lord has said "He that believeth
on me believeth not on me...

885
01:09:02,904 --> 01:09:05,146
but on him that sent me."

886
01:09:07,575 --> 01:09:10,742
"And if any man hear my words
and believe not...

887
01:09:12,205 --> 01:09:17,163
I judge him not.
For I came not to judge the world,

888
01:09:17,710 --> 01:09:20,248
but to save the world."

889
01:09:22,298 --> 01:09:24,540
Now is my soul troubled.

890
01:09:26,678 --> 01:09:28,884
But what shall I say?

891
01:09:30,348 --> 01:09:33,017
Shall I say "Father, save me"?

892
01:09:35,687 --> 01:09:40,645
But it is for this cause
that I came unto this hour.

893
01:09:47,365 --> 01:09:50,816
- Dearly beloved...
- (congregation) Dearly beloved...

894
01:09:50,952 --> 01:09:54,286
..avenge not yourselves, for it is written...

895
01:09:54,414 --> 01:09:55,825
..for it is written...

896
01:09:55,957 --> 01:09:59,077
- ..if thine enemy hunger...
- ..if thine enemy hunger...

897
01:09:59,210 --> 01:10:01,582
- ..feed him.
- ..feed him.

898
01:10:01,713 --> 01:10:04,334
- If he thirst...
- If he thirst...

899
01:10:04,465 --> 01:10:06,754
- ..give him drink.
- ..give him drink.

900
01:10:08,678 --> 01:10:13,174
- Be not overcome with evil...
- Be not overcome with evil...

901
01:10:13,308 --> 01:10:16,593
..but overcome evil with good.

902
01:10:16,811 --> 01:10:20,227
..but overcome evil with good.

903
01:10:20,356 --> 01:10:21,352
Amen.

904
01:10:21,483 --> 01:10:24,483
? Glory, glory, hallelujah

905
01:10:24,611 --> 01:10:28,443
? His truth is marching on

906
01:10:30,575 --> 01:10:32,614
(man) Hallelujah!

907
01:10:36,706 --> 01:10:38,746
Hallelujah, Sister!

908
01:10:54,933 --> 01:10:56,806
- Brother Gantry...
- Sister Rachel.

909
01:11:00,814 --> 01:11:03,221
She'll be out in a moment.

910
01:11:03,358 --> 01:11:06,193
Didn't I tell you?
Didn't I spot her genius first?

911
01:11:06,319 --> 01:11:09,688
There's been nothing like her
since Joan of Arc! I always say -

912
01:11:09,823 --> 01:11:15,113
and you can quote me on this one, boys -
there's nothing succeeds like success.

913
01:11:15,245 --> 01:11:18,779
- Let's get 'em outta here.
- A triumph over doubt and dissension.

914
01:11:18,915 --> 01:11:22,165
- Biggest thing in Christianity.
- Can I have a picture?

915
01:11:22,293 --> 01:11:25,164
Not me, and Sister's had
a tryin' ordeal, but thank you.

916
01:11:25,296 --> 01:11:27,538
I was saying, if it doesn't get you here...

917
01:11:27,674 --> 01:11:31,256
The poor child's practically out
on her feet. Let's give her a break.

918
01:11:31,386 --> 01:11:35,466
Sure. Sure. Sure. Come on, boys, let's
give the little lady a break, shall we?

919
01:11:35,598 --> 01:11:40,141
Time to say good night. We appreciated
all of you. Thanks for your cooperation.

920
01:11:40,270 --> 01:11:41,930
Good night, Sister.

921
01:11:43,523 --> 01:11:45,266
- Good night, Mr Morgan.
- Good night.

922
01:11:45,400 --> 01:11:47,108
- Good night, Bill.
- Mr Babbitt.

923
01:11:47,235 --> 01:11:51,731
- Never have made it without you.
- Thanks, Elmer. Good night. Good night.

924
01:11:51,865 --> 01:11:53,822
- Brother Gantry...
- Sister Rachel.

925
01:11:53,950 --> 01:11:57,485
Here's a young lady who deserves
your attention - our maestro of music.

926
01:11:57,620 --> 01:12:00,290
Captain Holt - a real Trojan.
Thank you. Good night.

927
01:12:00,415 --> 01:12:03,369
- Thank you, sir.
- Bill, I'll see if she needs anything.

928
01:12:03,501 --> 01:12:05,873
Gantry... thank you.

929
01:12:06,713 --> 01:12:08,373
Bill boy.

930
01:12:08,506 --> 01:12:11,176
- Yes. Yes.
- Good night.

931
01:12:11,301 --> 01:12:13,009
Bill boy. Yes.

932
01:12:13,136 --> 01:12:15,378
- Good night.
- Good night.

933
01:12:31,196 --> 01:12:32,820
Shara?

934
01:12:34,365 --> 01:12:36,405
Are you decent?

935
01:13:12,862 --> 01:13:14,902
Zenith Times-DisPatch? Just a moment.

936
01:13:15,031 --> 01:13:17,949
Slug this "Lead all, article one."

937
01:13:18,076 --> 01:13:20,911
Revivalism came to Zenith last night.

938
01:13:21,037 --> 01:13:26,162
After six years of backwoods success,
Sister Sharon Falconer -

939
01:13:26,292 --> 01:13:28,997
F-A-L-C-O-N-E-R -

940
01:13:29,128 --> 01:13:33,209
faced a fractious,
overflowing, metropolitan crowd.

941
01:13:33,341 --> 01:13:35,879
- Paragraph.
- (Phone rings)

942
01:13:36,010 --> 01:13:38,133
Jim Lefferts. Uh, later, please.

943
01:13:38,263 --> 01:13:40,635
- "Metropolitan crowd."
- Um...

944
01:13:40,765 --> 01:13:43,173
Many came to jeer...

945
01:13:43,309 --> 01:13:45,765
but stayed to cheer.

946
01:13:45,895 --> 01:13:50,688
Sister Sharon tamed the Philistines
with a simple prayer.

947
01:13:51,943 --> 01:13:56,404
The big-city hicks swallowed the
chocolate-coated pill with hosannas.

948
01:13:56,531 --> 01:14:00,149
- Give me a start on that, would you?
- Yeah, yeah.

949
01:14:00,285 --> 01:14:01,909
But...

950
01:14:03,079 --> 01:14:07,207
if simple prayer was
the main attraction of revivalism...

951
01:14:10,587 --> 01:14:16,173
Sister's tent would soon be as empty
as the churches she claims she can fill.

952
01:14:17,260 --> 01:14:18,885
Paragraph.

953
01:14:22,807 --> 01:14:25,477
What... is a revival?

954
01:14:27,270 --> 01:14:30,604
Is it a church? Is it a religion?

955
01:14:33,318 --> 01:14:36,069
Or is it a circus sideshow

956
01:14:36,196 --> 01:14:39,362
complete with freaks, magic,

957
01:14:39,491 --> 01:14:41,697
and rabble-rousing?

958
01:14:45,580 --> 01:14:49,281
Why does a revival attract thousands?

959
01:14:49,417 --> 01:14:53,664
To see a miracle? To be saved from
a lifetime of sin in five minutes?

960
01:14:53,796 --> 01:14:58,126
To be entertained, cured, cuddled,
in quick, painless salvation?

961
01:14:58,259 --> 01:14:59,884
Paragraph.

962
01:15:01,137 --> 01:15:06,262
Zenith is the heart of the Bible Belt. This
is an age that likes noise and whoopee.

963
01:15:06,392 --> 01:15:08,930
We're a fertile land
for corn, beans, squash,

964
01:15:09,062 --> 01:15:13,890
rumble-seat sex, and revivalism.
Hallelujah, brother.

965
01:15:16,903 --> 01:15:22,110
(Lefferts) What qualifies someone to be
a revivalist? Nothing Nothing at all

966
01:15:22,242 --> 01:15:24,815
There is not one law
in any state in the Union

967
01:15:24,953 --> 01:15:28,701
Protecting the Public from the
hysterical onslaught of revivalists

968
01:15:28,832 --> 01:15:33,292
But the law does Permit them
to invest in tax-free ProPerty,

969
01:15:33,419 --> 01:15:37,631
and collect money,
without accounting for how it is used

970
01:15:38,842 --> 01:15:41,511
What do you get for your money?
Can you get into heaven

971
01:15:41,636 --> 01:15:44,423
by contributing one buck or 50?

972
01:15:44,556 --> 01:15:48,719
Can you get life eternal by shaking hands
for Jesus with Elmer Gantry?

973
01:15:48,852 --> 01:15:51,425
"Continued on page three."

974
01:15:52,397 --> 01:15:54,021
So...

975
01:15:54,149 --> 01:15:59,605
"I watched this unholy trinity - Falconer,
Gantry, Morgan - save Nebraska."

976
01:15:59,737 --> 01:16:05,527
"Has sin in that state been washed away?
Is there less envy, lust or adultery?"

977
01:16:05,660 --> 01:16:07,202
- Ah.
- Gee, I hope not.

978
01:16:07,328 --> 01:16:10,495
- Break it up. A party of johns want action.
- Keep readin', honey.

979
01:16:10,623 --> 01:16:13,293
- But, Lulu, they'll be right over.
- Drop dead!

980
01:16:13,418 --> 01:16:16,123
- Cigarette me, Pete, honey.
- Honey, read!

981
01:16:16,921 --> 01:16:23,256
"To Elmer Gantry, God is an all-American
football player with a long white beard,

982
01:16:23,386 --> 01:16:27,598
who carries lightning in one hand,
and a bag of tricks in the other."

983
01:16:27,724 --> 01:16:31,638
"And Gantry has the high-pressure
style and personality to sell this God

984
01:16:31,769 --> 01:16:34,723
even to big-city slickers."

985
01:16:35,523 --> 01:16:38,608
"He can make
innocent people feel guilty...

986
01:16:39,486 --> 01:16:42,190
and bad people feel good."

987
01:16:42,322 --> 01:16:45,026
"Gantry has a voice made for promises."

988
01:16:45,158 --> 01:16:48,075
- Can he save anybody?
- Can he?

989
01:16:51,164 --> 01:16:55,114
Can he? Anywhere, any time.

990
01:16:55,251 --> 01:16:59,629
In a tent, standin' up,
layin' down, or any other way.

991
01:16:59,756 --> 01:17:02,081
And he's got plenty of ways!

992
01:17:02,217 --> 01:17:05,420
Lulu? Was you saved
by him, Lulu, honey?

993
01:17:05,553 --> 01:17:10,096
Sister, I was saved by him
way back in Schoenheim, Kansas.

994
01:17:10,225 --> 01:17:14,721
"Love... love is the mornin'
and the evenin' star."

995
01:17:14,854 --> 01:17:20,145
"And what is love?
Not the carnal, but the divine love!"

996
01:17:20,276 --> 01:17:23,811
Oh, he gave me special instructions
back of the pulpit Christmas Eve.

997
01:17:23,947 --> 01:17:26,698
He got to howlin' "Repent. Repent!"

998
01:17:26,825 --> 01:17:29,779
And I got to moanin' "Save me. Save me."

999
01:17:29,911 --> 01:17:34,869
He rammed the fear of God into me so
fast I never heard my old man's footsteps.

1000
01:17:34,999 --> 01:17:40,160
The next thing I knew, I was out in the
cold, hard snow in my bare little soul.

1001
01:17:41,798 --> 01:17:44,668
Oh, Brother Gantry, save me!

1002
01:17:55,270 --> 01:18:00,311
Don't do it, Shara. Don't get yourself
mixed up in an alley fight. Listen to me...

1003
01:18:00,441 --> 01:18:02,066
(click)

1004
01:18:04,863 --> 01:18:06,820
Why, Georgie, hello!

1005
01:18:06,948 --> 01:18:10,697
- You shut up. I am crucified to pieces.
- What's the matter?

1006
01:18:10,827 --> 01:18:14,362
What's the matter? "Why did
George F Babbitt underwrite a guarantee

1007
01:18:14,497 --> 01:18:16,822
of $30,000 to bring a revival to Zenith?"

1008
01:18:16,958 --> 01:18:19,793
"Is Sister Sharon
preaching the word of Jesus

1009
01:18:19,919 --> 01:18:23,371
or the gospel of Babbitt's
real-estate business?"

1010
01:18:23,506 --> 01:18:26,591
For God's sakes! I don't want any trouble.

1011
01:18:26,718 --> 01:18:30,466
I am in business.
I'm a 32nd-degree Mason.

1012
01:18:30,597 --> 01:18:33,301
George boy, don't take
this thing so seriously!

1013
01:18:33,433 --> 01:18:37,217
- I just sure as hell don't think it's a joke!
- We'll lick it, Georgie!

1014
01:18:37,353 --> 01:18:40,189
"Georgie!" My telephone
has not stopped ringing.

1015
01:18:40,315 --> 01:18:44,609
Everybody's mad at me or laughing at me.
Even my own family's turned against me.

1016
01:18:44,736 --> 01:18:46,360
As of right now,

1017
01:18:46,488 --> 01:18:50,984
I am cancelling out on my support -
financial and every other way.

1018
01:18:51,117 --> 01:18:53,691
George, you've got to fight back!

1019
01:18:56,664 --> 01:18:58,574
- Fight the press?
- Yes.

1020
01:18:58,708 --> 01:19:01,709
Mister, do you know anybody
ever licked the newspapers?

1021
01:19:01,836 --> 01:19:04,161
Me and you.

1022
01:19:04,297 --> 01:19:08,758
Besides, I am for a free press,
and for free enterprise,

1023
01:19:08,885 --> 01:19:12,420
and for... whatever the hell
the other freedoms are!

1024
01:19:12,555 --> 01:19:14,844
But, Reverend, you invited us here.

1025
01:19:14,974 --> 01:19:19,352
If you withdraw your support now, you're
endorsing this vicious newspaper smear.

1026
01:19:19,479 --> 01:19:21,970
- These telegrams of protest...
- There's always a lunatic fringe...

1027
01:19:22,106 --> 01:19:26,982
These are from my parishioners. These
are complaints from my church board.

1028
01:19:27,111 --> 01:19:30,563
Even my national superior
telephoned me long-distance.

1029
01:19:30,698 --> 01:19:32,774
I'm sorry, Mr Morgan.

1030
01:19:32,909 --> 01:19:35,993
- If you turn against us now...
- What I do doesn't matter.

1031
01:19:36,120 --> 01:19:39,489
Public opinion has turned against you.
That does matter.

1032
01:19:39,624 --> 01:19:43,242
- Tell him it's Sister Sharon Falconer.
- (knocking at door)

1033
01:19:43,378 --> 01:19:45,999
- No, I'll wait.
- (knocking)

1034
01:19:48,174 --> 01:19:51,009
- Did you find Mr Gantry?
- Nobody's seen him since he left.

1035
01:19:51,136 --> 01:19:53,805
- His hotel room?
- Hasn't been there all day.

1036
01:19:54,889 --> 01:19:57,427
Yes? Mr Eddington?

1037
01:19:58,476 --> 01:20:01,810
I want to see you. No, sir, at once.

1038
01:20:02,897 --> 01:20:07,643
No, your office will be fine.
Will you please have Mr Lefferts there?

1039
01:20:08,403 --> 01:20:10,442
Thank you.

1040
01:20:11,865 --> 01:20:15,280
Maybe... something
happened to Mr Gantry.

1041
01:20:15,410 --> 01:20:16,690
Forget Mr Gantry.

1042
01:20:41,019 --> 01:20:43,973
- Evening, George.
- I'm busy.

1043
01:20:44,105 --> 01:20:48,601
I had a busy day myself.
736 Lombard Street, two-storey building.

1044
01:20:48,735 --> 01:20:51,689
Owner: George F Babbitt.
Tenant: speakeasy.

1045
01:20:51,821 --> 01:20:56,198
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Of course. 1121 Maple Street.

1046
01:20:56,326 --> 01:20:59,576
Store front, apartment in rear.
Owner: George F Babbitt.

1047
01:20:59,704 --> 01:21:01,531
Business...

1048
01:21:03,249 --> 01:21:06,452
- Business: prostitution.
- On my property?

1049
01:21:06,586 --> 01:21:10,536
- Well, I'll have them evicted.
- Of course. Of course.

1050
01:21:10,673 --> 01:21:13,046
You've been victimised, George.

1051
01:21:13,176 --> 01:21:15,548
- Same as me.
- Yeah.

1052
01:21:16,930 --> 01:21:22,268
Evening, boys. Never bet into an open
pair... unless you've got the lock!

1053
01:21:23,478 --> 01:21:25,885
- Say good night, George.
- Oh, this?

1054
01:21:26,022 --> 01:21:30,601
Well, we're just playing for chips -
you know, sociable.

1055
01:21:30,735 --> 01:21:35,064
- You takin' me for a ride or somethin'?
- To the publisher of the Times-DisPatch

1056
01:21:35,198 --> 01:21:37,950
- You got somethin' on him, too?
- I got you.

1057
01:21:38,076 --> 01:21:40,946
- Yeah, sure, but...
- It's getting late, George.

1058
01:21:41,079 --> 01:21:44,364
The point is, why did he write this trash,
and why did you publish it?

1059
01:21:44,499 --> 01:21:47,453
- Are you suggesting censorship, Miss?
- Only fair play.

1060
01:21:47,585 --> 01:21:49,792
- This is muckraking!
- Is it true?

1061
01:21:49,921 --> 01:21:51,712
- No!
- Then sue us for libel.

1062
01:21:51,840 --> 01:21:56,133
Oh, you're much too clever for that.
It's what you imply - the veiled slurs.

1063
01:21:56,261 --> 01:21:59,546
- Hints that I misused collection money.
- I never said that.

1064
01:21:59,681 --> 01:22:03,678
Did I ever preach anything
but God's word? Well? Did I?

1065
01:22:03,810 --> 01:22:05,968
- Are you ordained?
- What?

1066
01:22:06,104 --> 01:22:09,971
Do you hold a degree from any
recognised theological seminary?

1067
01:22:10,108 --> 01:22:13,025
- Does Gantry?
- No.

1068
01:22:13,153 --> 01:22:16,356
Are you sanctioned
to preach by any church?

1069
01:22:16,489 --> 01:22:21,447
No, Mr Lefferts, but... neither was Peter
or Paul or any of the other apostles.

1070
01:22:21,578 --> 01:22:25,243
Ah, but they said that they lived with
the Son of God, were taught by him,

1071
01:22:25,373 --> 01:22:27,781
were sanctified by him.

1072
01:22:27,917 --> 01:22:31,417
What gives you
the right to speak for God?

1073
01:22:35,842 --> 01:22:39,341
I couldn't possibly be doing
God's work without his approval.

1074
01:22:39,471 --> 01:22:41,843
How did you get his approval?

1075
01:22:43,975 --> 01:22:46,596
Did God speak to you personally?

1076
01:22:48,813 --> 01:22:51,185
Did he send you a letter?

1077
01:22:52,233 --> 01:22:54,724
Did you have a visitation from God?

1078
01:22:54,861 --> 01:22:57,103
A burning bush, perhaps?

1079
01:22:59,157 --> 01:23:04,317
Where in the New Testament does it say
that God spoke to anyone except his son?

1080
01:23:07,207 --> 01:23:09,876
But it does say in the First Corinthians

1081
01:23:10,001 --> 01:23:13,417
"Let your women
keep silence in the churches."

1082
01:23:13,546 --> 01:23:16,381
"It is a shame for women
to speak in the church."

1083
01:23:16,508 --> 01:23:20,552
Congratulations, Jim boy. I see you're
a student of the Bible. I'm delighted.

1084
01:23:20,678 --> 01:23:25,139
What is it? Are you responsible for some
of these crackpot calls I've been getting?

1085
01:23:25,266 --> 01:23:28,470
- You want Mr Lefferts fired, too?
- Fired?

1086
01:23:28,603 --> 01:23:31,604
Why, I'd give Jim a bonus
for boostin' circulation.

1087
01:23:31,731 --> 01:23:34,103
I thought you came to bury Caesar,
not to praise him.

1088
01:23:34,234 --> 01:23:39,228
Shakespeare. Ah, yes. A moment ago you
used the Bible... to whip Sister Sharon.

1089
01:23:39,364 --> 01:23:43,231
- I merely quoted it as a source.
- Of course. As a good newspaperman,

1090
01:23:43,368 --> 01:23:46,701
you wouldn't use information
unless it was fact, would you?

1091
01:23:46,830 --> 01:23:49,581
Tell me somethin', Jim.

1092
01:23:49,707 --> 01:23:51,700
Is the Bible fact?

1093
01:23:51,835 --> 01:23:53,115
Hm?

1094
01:23:53,253 --> 01:23:56,787
Well, come on, Jim boy.
Did God create the universe in six days?

1095
01:23:56,923 --> 01:24:00,374
Did He make the sun stand still
to help Joshua lick the Amalekites?

1096
01:24:00,510 --> 01:24:02,052
No.

1097
01:24:02,178 --> 01:24:04,467
- You don't believe Moses parted the sea?
- No.

1098
01:24:04,597 --> 01:24:07,883
- God wrote the Ten Commandments?
- Nope.

1099
01:24:08,017 --> 01:24:10,769
Or that the dead were raised
and the blind cured?

1100
01:24:10,895 --> 01:24:14,430
And 5,000 people were fed
with five little fishes

1101
01:24:14,566 --> 01:24:16,891
and two little itty-bitty loaves of bread?

1102
01:24:17,026 --> 01:24:18,106
No.

1103
01:24:18,236 --> 01:24:21,652
You don't believe in any of the miracles
in the Holy Bible, do you?

1104
01:24:21,781 --> 01:24:26,692
No more than I believe that black cats or
spilt salt or broken mirrors are bad luck.

1105
01:24:26,828 --> 01:24:31,324
Or that God can be jealous
or bloodthirsty or vengeful.

1106
01:24:31,457 --> 01:24:35,586
Or that Jehovah sanctions bigamy
and stupidity and slavery.

1107
01:24:35,712 --> 01:24:38,962
In other words,
you don't believe in the Bible.

1108
01:24:40,175 --> 01:24:44,042
I believe that the Bible is a book
of beautiful poetry and wisdom...

1109
01:24:44,179 --> 01:24:46,218
But it's not fact.

1110
01:24:49,517 --> 01:24:50,762
And if it's not fact,

1111
01:24:50,894 --> 01:24:54,512
why would he use it as information,
except to destroy her character?

1112
01:24:54,647 --> 01:24:58,147
I heard you say it,
and you'll burn in hell for it.

1113
01:24:58,276 --> 01:25:01,562
No, Georgie.
You can't scare Jim that way.

1114
01:25:02,697 --> 01:25:08,617
You see, if you don't believe in the Bible...
you don't believe there's a real hell.

1115
01:25:08,745 --> 01:25:09,943
Hey.

1116
01:25:10,079 --> 01:25:14,208
And it follows if there's no real hell, there
can't be a real heaven. Right, Jim boy?

1117
01:25:14,334 --> 01:25:17,370
Why don't you get to the point?

1118
01:25:17,504 --> 01:25:21,632
Do you believe Jesus Christ
can give us life everlasting?

1119
01:25:29,641 --> 01:25:33,769
Do you believe Jesus Christ
can give us life everlasting?

1120
01:25:36,272 --> 01:25:39,059
- I'd love to believe it.
- But you don't?

1121
01:25:40,109 --> 01:25:41,734
No.

1122
01:25:45,740 --> 01:25:49,441
Then you don't accept
Jesus Christ as divine, do you?

1123
01:26:00,505 --> 01:26:01,501
Well?

1124
01:26:04,843 --> 01:26:10,347
Jesus was a great, virtuous teacher.
His faith and courage changed the world.

1125
01:26:10,473 --> 01:26:13,510
Do you accept Jesus Christ as divine?

1126
01:26:17,647 --> 01:26:21,063
Let me say... I have doubts.

1127
01:26:21,192 --> 01:26:25,404
- That's blasphemy!
- Mr Babbitt, to doubt is not blasphemy.

1128
01:26:25,530 --> 01:26:29,362
When you say "blasphemy", you mean
"Don't dare disagree. Don't think."

1129
01:26:29,492 --> 01:26:31,651
"Don't doubt."

1130
01:26:31,786 --> 01:26:37,243
But Tolstoy, Darwin, Jefferson, Lincoln -
they had the same doubts.

1131
01:26:37,375 --> 01:26:40,044
Then they'll burn in hell, too!

1132
01:26:40,962 --> 01:26:44,794
Mr Eddington, in spite of
Mr Lefferts' confessed bigotry,

1133
01:26:44,924 --> 01:26:48,589
I defend your right to publish these
articles. But give us equal rights.

1134
01:26:48,720 --> 01:26:52,848
- Your reply'll be published prominently.
- Mr Eddington, I'm no writer.

1135
01:26:52,974 --> 01:26:56,224
Now, Jim is brilliant and witty.
Uses words like a stiletto.

1136
01:26:56,352 --> 01:26:59,971
He learned from Mencken, Ingersoll,
Sinclair Lewis, other atheists.

1137
01:27:00,106 --> 01:27:02,348
- Atheists!
- But you own a radio station.

1138
01:27:02,484 --> 01:27:05,438
Set the time. Half an hour.
Tonight? Tomorrow? Name it.

1139
01:27:05,570 --> 01:27:09,188
Every day for two weeks -
half-hour in the morning and evening.

1140
01:27:09,324 --> 01:27:14,033
- Just to answer this article?
- I don't intend to answer anything.

1141
01:27:14,162 --> 01:27:16,201
You don't debate the existence of God.

1142
01:27:16,331 --> 01:27:19,747
Jim, here, has spread
the poison of doubt and disbelief.

1143
01:27:19,876 --> 01:27:24,668
Just give me a chance to spread the
gospel, to raise the banner of Christianity,

1144
01:27:24,797 --> 01:27:27,668
to restore the faith he stole.

1145
01:27:27,801 --> 01:27:31,419
Now, sir, I realise time means money -
especially radio time.

1146
01:27:31,554 --> 01:27:33,428
Right.

1147
01:27:34,224 --> 01:27:36,465
So our good citizen, George F Babbitt,

1148
01:27:36,601 --> 01:27:41,596
