1365
01:45:14,367 --> 01:45:16,739
- You look swell, kid.
- Likewise.

1366
01:45:16,870 --> 01:45:18,909
Just swell.

1367
01:45:28,423 --> 01:45:31,092
- Sorry about last night.
- Forget it.

1368
01:45:35,680 --> 01:45:39,678
- If I'd known I'd run into you, I'd have...
- Oh, that's OK.

1369
01:45:51,362 --> 01:45:53,853
- What the hell's the big idea?
- Elmer, honey...

1370
01:45:53,990 --> 01:45:58,237
- You think I'll sit still for a shakedown?
- How could I put the squeeze on you?

1371
01:45:58,369 --> 01:46:02,450
- Who'll take the word of a hooker?
- The old badger game, huh?

1372
01:46:02,582 --> 01:46:05,583
- I only wanted to see you for...
- For what?

1373
01:46:05,710 --> 01:46:07,952
- Well, for...
- For what?

1374
01:46:09,088 --> 01:46:14,712
Gee, honey, look. Look, I'm almost
packed. The cops gave me notice.

1375
01:46:14,844 --> 01:46:17,514
I got a ticket on the midnight bus.

1376
01:46:30,819 --> 01:46:33,060
I got no beef against you.

1377
01:46:34,197 --> 01:46:37,151
I only wanted to see you once more,

1378
01:46:37,283 --> 01:46:41,411
kick around some old memories,
maybe have a few laughs.

1379
01:46:41,538 --> 01:46:43,577
Go on.

1380
01:46:48,503 --> 01:46:50,709
Who am I kiddin'?

1381
01:46:52,131 --> 01:46:56,628
When you first hit town, I figured
you could go to hell without my help.

1382
01:46:56,761 --> 01:47:00,629
When you came bustin' in last night
like God Almighty wearin' a tin star,

1383
01:47:00,765 --> 01:47:05,926
I got mad, boilin' mad. All I could think of
was how you took me and ditched me.

1384
01:47:06,062 --> 01:47:09,811
That's all I could think of.
Me, little Miss Lulu, the dumb pushover.

1385
01:47:09,941 --> 01:47:12,693
And when the cops said
"Get out of town in 24 hours",

1386
01:47:12,819 --> 01:47:15,144
all I wanted to do was spit in your eye,

1387
01:47:15,280 --> 01:47:18,814
blackmail you, a shakedown -
anything to hurt you.

1388
01:47:21,369 --> 01:47:22,994
But...

1389
01:47:24,622 --> 01:47:27,292
But when you walked in just now...

1390
01:47:29,544 --> 01:47:31,999
Gee, honey...

1391
01:47:32,130 --> 01:47:35,629
it was like the first time
between us all over again.

1392
01:47:37,218 --> 01:47:39,674
All goose pimples and...

1393
01:47:44,350 --> 01:47:46,473
You'd better beat it.

1394
01:47:48,521 --> 01:47:50,763
I'm sorry I phoned.

1395
01:47:51,774 --> 01:47:54,941
I won't make any trouble.
Not even if I could.

1396
01:47:58,490 --> 01:48:00,731
Please go now.

1397
01:48:04,871 --> 01:48:08,287
I did run out on you
back there in Kansas, didn't I?

1398
01:48:09,584 --> 01:48:13,285
It's nobody's fault.
Except maybe my old man's.

1399
01:48:13,421 --> 01:48:16,173
- Ever hear from him?
- Once, last Christmas.

1400
01:48:16,299 --> 01:48:21,638
The letter said "Daughter, read
1st Kings, Chapter 21, Verse 23."

1401
01:48:21,763 --> 01:48:27,006
I looked it up. It said "And the dogs
in the street shall eat Jezebel."

1402
01:48:28,853 --> 01:48:31,225
My old man and his Bible.

1403
01:48:32,857 --> 01:48:34,897
Tell me...

1404
01:48:35,735 --> 01:48:39,151
how is it some people can
only find hate in the Bible?

1405
01:48:43,660 --> 01:48:48,369
- Where will you be going to?
- I think I'll go tramping through Paris.

1406
01:48:48,498 --> 01:48:51,582
Can you use some cash?
Sort of tide you over?

1407
01:48:56,714 --> 01:48:59,466
Just... just kiss me goodbye.

1408
01:49:00,802 --> 01:49:02,676
Just once.

1409
01:49:46,222 --> 01:49:48,262
What's she doin'?

1410
01:49:58,443 --> 01:50:00,482
Stay awhile.

1411
01:50:02,655 --> 01:50:04,695
Talk to me.

1412
01:50:06,034 --> 01:50:08,821
Oh, don't go yet. Please don't go.

1413
01:50:11,581 --> 01:50:13,787
Tell me anything.

1414
01:50:13,917 --> 01:50:17,499
Tell me a good, strong lie
I can believe, but hold me.

1415
01:50:17,629 --> 01:50:20,583
Just hold me like you used to.

1416
01:50:20,715 --> 01:50:22,340
Please.

1417
01:50:36,981 --> 01:50:39,270
- No use, Lu.
- Why?

1418
01:50:39,400 --> 01:50:41,440
Because I...

1419
01:50:42,320 --> 01:50:46,567
- I don't know. I...
- Because of what? Because of her?

1420
01:50:46,699 --> 01:50:48,359
That Bible broad?

1421
01:51:06,344 --> 01:51:08,882
I'm sorry. No hard feelings.

1422
01:51:10,014 --> 01:51:13,218
- Please. Don't go yet.
- Lu, I...

1423
01:51:13,351 --> 01:51:17,728
You know, I... I could use
some of that cash after all.

1424
01:51:18,690 --> 01:51:24,810
Why, sure. Maybe I could send you some
from time to time. Till you get a job, or...

1425
01:51:24,946 --> 01:51:28,196
or maybe meet some nice
respectable man, huh?

1426
01:51:28,324 --> 01:51:31,195
I meet nice respectable men every night.

1427
01:51:36,416 --> 01:51:38,788
The best bank in America.

1428
01:51:45,925 --> 01:51:48,796
- Take care of yourself.
- Likewise, hon.

1429
01:51:52,640 --> 01:51:55,844
Class. She's got real class.

1430
01:52:11,659 --> 01:52:14,197
Wake up! Wake up, Miss Katie Jones!

1431
01:52:15,705 --> 01:52:20,747
You see before you the captain of the
SS HaPPiness, fishing boat extraordinary.

1432
01:52:20,877 --> 01:52:24,495
All aboard for a glorious,
carefree, happy cruise.

1433
01:52:24,631 --> 01:52:28,082
Fun, fish, frolic... and romance.

1434
01:52:28,802 --> 01:52:30,461
Guaranteed.

1435
01:52:36,226 --> 01:52:38,265
(knocking at door)

1436
01:52:39,729 --> 01:52:42,018
(knocking)

1437
01:52:42,440 --> 01:52:44,682
(Persistent knocking)

1438
01:52:54,202 --> 01:52:59,956
Bill! Not one word, not one, about legal
documents, tents, moneys or lost souls.

1439
01:53:00,083 --> 01:53:03,618
We're going on a picnic, see,
and if you squeal, we'll rub you out.

1440
01:53:03,753 --> 01:53:05,995
Do you think I'd rat on a couple of pals?

1441
01:53:06,130 --> 01:53:08,503
It will be all right, won't it, for one day?

1442
01:53:08,633 --> 01:53:11,634
In that outfit, the fish'll jump
into the boat to look at you.

1443
01:53:11,761 --> 01:53:13,386
Yes.

1444
01:53:14,514 --> 01:53:17,468
We're going! We're going on a picnic!

1445
01:53:18,560 --> 01:53:21,644
I've been promising
to take her on a picnic.

1446
01:53:23,189 --> 01:53:26,143
You got that look, Bill. What's the matter?

1447
01:53:37,787 --> 01:53:40,954
Elmer the Great. Elmer the Grifter.

1448
01:53:41,082 --> 01:53:45,543
The con man conned with
the oldest badger game in the world.

1449
01:53:45,670 --> 01:53:48,291
- I don't want Shara to see these.
- She'll have to.

1450
01:53:48,423 --> 01:53:52,634
Bill, I'll do anything you say.
I'll... I'll quit. I...

1451
01:53:53,386 --> 01:53:55,924
- Don't let Shara see these.
- She's got to see them.

1452
01:53:56,264 --> 01:54:00,890
Darling, don't you think we ought
to take Bill on the picnic with us?

1453
01:54:40,683 --> 01:54:42,308
I...

1454
01:54:45,104 --> 01:54:48,639
- I suppose they're for sale?
- $25,000.

1455
01:54:50,985 --> 01:54:53,108
25,000.

1456
01:54:53,530 --> 01:54:56,899
Two o'clock today. Cash. In small bills.

1457
01:54:57,033 --> 01:55:01,327
And she wants Shara
to bring her the money, nobody else.

1458
01:55:06,417 --> 01:55:08,659
Her name is Lulu Bains.

1459
01:55:20,098 --> 01:55:22,137
Get the money.

1460
01:55:25,562 --> 01:55:29,511
One more thing. She wants you to bring
the money to 721 Lombard Street.

1461
01:55:29,649 --> 01:55:32,852
That's where she worked
before it was raided.

1462
01:55:44,455 --> 01:55:47,540
(woman) Sammy! Get out of the water!

1463
01:55:55,550 --> 01:55:57,589
(? honky-tonk Piano)

1464
01:56:26,789 --> 01:56:28,782
(cat yowls)

1465
01:56:29,751 --> 01:56:32,289
Make yourself right at home, honey.

1466
01:56:52,982 --> 01:56:55,022
Be right there!

1467
01:56:55,318 --> 01:56:57,358
(cat meows)

1468
01:57:12,335 --> 01:57:14,375
(yowls)

1469
01:57:29,978 --> 01:57:32,220
I've brought the money.

1470
01:57:34,524 --> 01:57:36,766
May I have the negatives, please?

1471
01:57:52,333 --> 01:57:54,373
Extra, Jack!

1472
01:57:56,838 --> 01:58:01,666
Yeah. Yeah, I read the story,
I saw the pictures.

1473
01:58:01,801 --> 01:58:04,672
- Thank you very much.
- Did you see this?

1474
01:58:06,055 --> 01:58:08,095
I saw it.

1475
01:58:08,725 --> 01:58:11,263
- Did you see this?
- Yeah.

1476
01:58:11,394 --> 01:58:14,680
Now, I understand she brought
these pictures to you first.

1477
01:58:14,814 --> 01:58:16,688
- Yeah.
- And you turned her down?

1478
01:58:16,816 --> 01:58:18,441
Mm-hm.

1479
01:58:22,405 --> 01:58:24,030
Why?

1480
01:58:25,074 --> 01:58:29,368
These pictures prove only one thing -
that Gantry's as human as anybody else.

1481
01:58:29,496 --> 01:58:31,951
It's the obligation of a free press to print...

1482
01:58:32,081 --> 01:58:36,660
You're right, Mr Eddington. A free press
can print anything, including lies.

1483
01:58:36,794 --> 01:58:41,421
And that's exactly what
that pornography is: blackmailing lies.

1484
01:58:43,885 --> 01:58:45,924
(? "Abide With Me")

1485
01:58:57,315 --> 01:59:00,565
Why don't those men take off their hats?

1486
01:59:25,718 --> 01:59:28,554
First time I've seen
Reverend Pengilly up there.

1487
01:59:28,680 --> 01:59:31,799
First time they've ever
been in trouble up there.

1488
01:59:37,063 --> 01:59:40,266
Thank you for coming here tonight.

1489
01:59:41,192 --> 01:59:44,526
You have every right to an explanation.

1490
01:59:45,196 --> 01:59:47,734
I will try to give it to you.

1491
01:59:48,074 --> 01:59:50,363
Tell us about sin, Sister!

1492
01:59:50,493 --> 01:59:53,743
(woman) Antichrist! You Judas, you!

1493
01:59:53,872 --> 01:59:56,078
- You false prophet!
- You faker, you!

1494
01:59:56,207 --> 01:59:58,200
- Boo!
- Yeah!

1495
01:59:58,334 --> 02:00:03,791
- Liar! Damn your own soul, Mr Gantry!
- You call yourself a preacher?

1496
02:00:08,219 --> 02:00:10,046
Come on, Rachel.

1497
02:00:15,935 --> 02:00:18,058
Rachel, you've gotta get outta here.

1498
02:00:18,354 --> 02:00:21,854
(trumPeter Plays jazz version
of "Onward Christian Soldiers")

1499
02:01:02,065 --> 02:01:04,437
Hey, Mr Gantry!

1500
02:01:38,434 --> 02:01:40,474
(Phones ringing)

1501
02:01:58,371 --> 02:02:00,992
- Hello?
- My name is Mrs Welmer

1502
02:02:01,124 --> 02:02:03,793
I go to church every Sunday

1503
02:02:05,253 --> 02:02:07,709
You tell that Sister Sharon

1504
02:02:20,310 --> 02:02:24,639
- Get outta town, preacher woman!
- Go home, Sister!

1505
02:02:24,772 --> 02:02:26,812
- Poor Sister!
- (laughter)

1506
02:02:35,200 --> 02:02:37,525
O my God...

1507
02:02:39,078 --> 02:02:41,320
why hast thou forsaken me?

1508
02:02:46,252 --> 02:02:48,459
We'll take you home.

1509
02:03:20,745 --> 02:03:22,868
Why'd you do it?

1510
02:03:23,957 --> 02:03:26,163
Did... did she show with the money?

1511
02:03:27,252 --> 02:03:28,876
Well?

1512
02:03:30,213 --> 02:03:31,837
Yes.

1513
02:03:34,217 --> 02:03:37,384
Why didn't you go through with it? Why?

1514
02:03:39,806 --> 02:03:42,048
You wouldn't understand.

1515
02:03:50,150 --> 02:03:53,768
I know. You took
the pictures to the paper

1516
02:03:53,903 --> 02:03:56,655
cos they were gonna pay you more, huh?

1517
02:03:56,781 --> 02:03:58,857
How much did you get for 'em?

1518
02:03:58,992 --> 02:04:00,700
Nothing.

1519
02:04:00,827 --> 02:04:02,866
I didn't sell them.

1520
02:04:06,457 --> 02:04:09,127
You were never gonna sell 'em...

1521
02:04:09,252 --> 02:04:12,206
not even to that Sister woman, were you?

1522
02:04:12,338 --> 02:04:15,292
You hate Gantry that much?

1523
02:04:15,425 --> 02:04:18,046
Or do you love him that much?

1524
02:04:22,432 --> 02:04:25,053
And you're no good to me.

1525
02:04:25,185 --> 02:04:27,510
Or yourself.

1526
02:04:27,645 --> 02:04:30,101
You're no good to anybody!

1527
02:04:31,149 --> 02:04:32,643
(slaP)

1528
02:04:32,859 --> 02:04:33,772
(slaP)

1529
02:04:43,536 --> 02:04:46,206
Don't you know that hurts?

1530
02:06:05,869 --> 02:06:08,442
I'm sorry, Lu.

1531
02:06:08,580 --> 02:06:10,952
I'm sorry for everything.

1532
02:07:08,014 --> 02:07:10,256
Brothers and sisters...

1533
02:07:12,101 --> 02:07:13,560
goodbye.

1534
02:07:13,686 --> 02:07:14,766
Amen.

1535
02:07:17,106 --> 02:07:18,221
Jim boy!

1536
02:07:18,358 --> 02:07:21,359
You look like a man
who could use a drink.

1537
02:07:21,486 --> 02:07:27,240
Booze. You know somethin', Jim?
There oughta be a law against drinkin'.

1538
02:07:27,367 --> 02:07:30,652
- There is. Prohibition.
- That's against sellin', not drinkin'.

1539
02:07:30,787 --> 02:07:32,198
Amen.

1540
02:07:33,039 --> 02:07:35,577
- Happy days!
- I'll drink to that.

1541
02:07:37,502 --> 02:07:39,541
God, that's good.

1542
02:07:42,090 --> 02:07:44,497
Would you look at this place, Jim?

1543
02:07:47,220 --> 02:07:50,470
What were they so mad about, anyhow?

1544
02:07:50,598 --> 02:07:54,098
The mob don't like
their gods to be human.

1545
02:07:54,227 --> 02:07:57,560
- They hurt you?
- Not as much as you hurt me.

1546
02:07:57,689 --> 02:08:00,262
Nothing personal.

1547
02:08:00,400 --> 02:08:03,151
What'll you do now?

1548
02:08:03,278 --> 02:08:07,489
Well, the way I got it figured, you're up,
you're down, you sin, you're saved.

1549
02:08:07,615 --> 02:08:11,115
You do the best you can,
and you leave the rest to the Lord.

1550
02:08:11,244 --> 02:08:13,949
You really do believe
in the Lord, don't you?

1551
02:08:14,080 --> 02:08:18,872
Damn right I do. It does a man good
to get down on his knees once in a while.

1552
02:08:19,002 --> 02:08:21,409
That's why people
come to a place like this,

1553
02:08:21,546 --> 02:08:26,374
because they're scared, or sick,
or... because they got no money,

1554
02:08:26,509 --> 02:08:30,210
or too much money.
Or before a war, or after a war.

1555
02:08:32,140 --> 02:08:36,268
Praying's the cheapest
first-rate medicine I know.

1556
02:08:36,394 --> 02:08:38,850
That's why Shara was so good for them.

1557
02:08:41,483 --> 02:08:43,724
She's a lotta woman.

1558
02:08:45,904 --> 02:08:47,528
Yeah.

1559
02:08:48,990 --> 02:08:51,315
You oughta marry her.

1560
02:08:51,451 --> 02:08:56,611
- You believe in holy matrimony?
- I can recommend it, never having tried it.

1561
02:08:57,707 --> 02:09:00,079
Too late now, Jim boy.

1562
02:09:01,085 --> 02:09:03,125
Maybe not.

1563
02:09:04,047 --> 02:09:08,044
Miss Bains was waiting for me
at the paper with that story.

1564
02:09:20,146 --> 02:09:23,064
- How'd you get her to do it?
- I didn't.

1565
02:09:25,568 --> 02:09:28,439
The Lord sure moves in mysterious ways.

1566
02:09:35,537 --> 02:09:40,080
Any minute now, you will hear
the voice of Sister Sharon Falconer,

1567
02:09:40,208 --> 02:09:42,616
but not that, I'm afraid, of Elmer Gantry.

1568
02:09:42,961 --> 02:09:46,495
For Mr Gantry has completely vanished
since three nights ago.

1569
02:09:46,631 --> 02:09:49,881
I've checked the police,
hospitals, railroads, bus depots...

1570
02:09:50,009 --> 02:09:51,552
Where is he? Where?

1571
02:09:51,678 --> 02:09:56,803
Every wire service in the country's asking
the same question. He's page-one news.

1572
02:09:56,933 --> 02:10:00,017
If anything happened to him,
you'd know it.

1573
02:10:04,482 --> 02:10:06,107
Yes.

1574
02:10:07,235 --> 02:10:09,477
Yes, I would know it.

1575
02:10:11,865 --> 02:10:15,993
He'll be here, I'm... I'm sure of it.
We'll wait for him.

1576
02:10:16,119 --> 02:10:21,623
We can't wait. Some of those people
have been out there since early morning.

1577
02:10:21,749 --> 02:10:25,249
- I won't go on without him.
- Maybe he won't be back.

1578
02:10:27,755 --> 02:10:29,795
Just a feeling.

1579
02:10:34,179 --> 02:10:36,136
We'll wait for him.

1580
02:10:41,769 --> 02:10:44,854
(congregation sings
"Onward Christian Soldiers")

1581
02:11:08,630 --> 02:11:10,254
Elmer?

1582
02:11:16,429 --> 02:11:18,173
Oh, darling!

1583
02:11:18,306 --> 02:11:20,049
Darling!

1584
02:11:21,893 --> 02:11:23,720
- Gantry's back.
- How do you know?

1585
02:11:23,853 --> 02:11:27,554
Somebody just saw him.
Where's a phone around here?

1586
02:11:28,233 --> 02:11:32,100
- What about your friend Gantry?
- Quite a guy! Son of a...

1587
02:11:32,237 --> 02:11:34,478
(band Plays fanfare)

1588
02:11:36,574 --> 02:11:38,863
Let me look at you.

1589
02:11:38,993 --> 02:11:41,994
Three endless days without a word.

1590
02:11:42,121 --> 02:11:43,865
Why?

1591
02:11:43,998 --> 02:11:47,533
Don't you realise how much I need you?

1592
02:11:50,338 --> 02:11:53,173
Are you angry? With me?

1593
02:11:53,299 --> 02:11:56,585
- No, Shara.
- Don't ever leave me again. Ever.

1594
02:11:58,304 --> 02:12:00,262
Shara.

1595
02:12:00,390 --> 02:12:02,014
Yes?

1596
02:12:03,268 --> 02:12:05,640
What would happen if we chucked it all,

1597
02:12:05,770 --> 02:12:09,934
beat it across the state line,
get good and married, like most folks?

1598
02:12:10,066 --> 02:12:14,395
Have a bunch of kids, take 'em
to a ball game like most folks.

1599
02:12:14,529 --> 02:12:19,570
Go dancin'. We've never gone
dancin' together, not even once.

1600
02:12:19,701 --> 02:12:22,156
Let's do it, Shara. Tonight. Right now.

1601
02:12:22,287 --> 02:12:25,786
- But all those people...
- If they wanna pray...

1602
02:12:26,666 --> 02:12:29,239
let 'em go to church.

1603
02:12:29,377 --> 02:12:31,002
But...

1604
02:12:32,505 --> 02:12:34,747
this is their church.

